  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah Denounces Ahaziah'
      title: Elijah Denounces Ahaziah
      number: 1
      content: '    After the death of Ahab, Moab rebelled against Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now Ahaziah fell through the lattice in his upper chamber in Samaria,
        and lay sick; so he sent messengers, telling them, \u201CGo, inquire of Baal-zebub,
        the god of Ekron, whether I shall recover from this sickness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Elijah the
        Tishbite, \u201CArise, go up to meet the messengers of the king of Samaria,
        and say to them, \u2018Is it because there is no God in Israel that you are
        going to inquire of Baal-zebub, the god of Ekron? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, You shall
        not come down from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall surely
        die.\u2019\u201D So Elijah went.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The messengers returned to the king, and he said to them, \u201CWhy
        have you returned?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CThere came a man to meet us, and said
        to us, \u2018Go back to the king who sent you, and say to him, Thus says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, Is it because there is no God in Israel
        that you are sending to inquire of Baal-zebub, the god of Ekron? Therefore
        you shall not come down from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall
        surely die.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He said to them, \u201CWhat kind of man was he who came to meet you
        and told you these things?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They answered him, \u201CHe wore a garment of hair, with a belt of
        leather about his waist.\u201D And he said, \u201CIt is Elijah the Tishbite.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the king sent to him a captain of fifty men with his fifty.
        He went up to Elijah, who was sitting on the top of a hill, and said to him,
        \u201CO man of God, the king says, \u2018Come down.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Elijah answered the captain of fifty, \u201CIf I am a man of
        God, let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty.\u201D
        Then fire came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Again the king sent to him another captain of fifty men with his
        fifty. And he answered and said to him, \u201CO man of God, this is the king\u2019s
        order, \u2018Come down quickly!\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But Elijah answered them, \u201CIf I am a man of God, let fire come
        down from heaven and consume you and your fifty.\u201D Then the fire of God
        came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Again the king sent the captain of a third fifty with his fifty.
        And the third captain of fifty went up and came and fell on his knees before
        Elijah and entreated him, \u201CO man of God, please let my life, and the
        life of these fifty servants of yours, be precious in your sight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Behold, fire came down from heaven and consumed the two former captains
        of fifty men with their fifties, but now let my life be precious in your
        sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Elijah,
        \u201CGo down with him; do not be afraid of him.\u201D So he arose and went
        down with him to the king "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and said to him, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u2018Because you have sent messengers to inquire of Baal-zebub, the god
        of Ekron\u2014is it because there is no God in Israel to inquire of his word?\u2014therefore
        you shall not come down from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall
        surely die.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So he died according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        that Elijah had spoken. Jehoram became king in his place in the second year
        of Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat, king of Judah, because Ahaziah had no
        son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Now the rest of the acts of Ahaziah that he did, are they not written
        in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah Taken to Heaven'
      title: Elijah Taken to Heaven
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was about to take Elijah
        up to heaven by a whirlwind, Elijah and Elisha were on their way from Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Elijah said to Elisha, \u201CPlease stay here, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has sent me as far as Bethel.\u201D But Elisha said, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.\u201D So they went
        down to Bethel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the sons of the prophets who were in Bethel came out to Elisha
        and said to him, \u201CDo you know that today the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will take away your master from over you?\u201D And he said, \u201CYes, I
        know it; keep quiet.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Elijah said to him, \u201CElisha, please stay here, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has sent me to Jericho.\u201D But he said, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.\u201D So they came
        to Jericho. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The sons of the prophets who were at Jericho drew near to Elisha
        and said to him, \u201CDo you know that today the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will take away your master from over you?\u201D And he answered, \u201CYes,
        I know it; keep quiet.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Elijah said to him, \u201CPlease stay here, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has sent me to the Jordan.\u201D But he said, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.\u201D So the two of
        them went on. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Fifty men of the sons of the prophets also went and stood at some
        distance from them, as they both were standing by the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then Elijah took his cloak and rolled it up and struck the water,
        and the water was parted to the one side and to the other, till the two of
        them could go over on dry ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When they had crossed, Elijah said to Elisha, \u201CAsk what I shall
        do for you, before I am taken from you.\u201D And Elisha said, \u201CPlease
        let there be a double portion of your spirit on me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he said, \u201CYou have asked a hard thing; yet, if you see me
        as I am being taken from you, it shall be so for you, but if you do not see
        me, it shall not be so.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And as they still went on and talked, behold, chariots of fire and
        horses of fire separated the two of them. And Elijah went up by a whirlwind
        into heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Elisha saw it and he cried, \u201CMy father, my father! The chariots
        of Israel and its horsemen!\u201D And he saw him no more.Then he took hold
        of his own clothes and tore them in two pieces. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he took up the cloak of Elijah that had fallen from him and went
        back and stood on the bank of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Elisha Succeeds Elijah'
      title: Elisha Succeeds Elijah
      number: 14
      content: "Then he took the cloak of Elijah that had fallen from him and struck
        the water, saying, \u201CWhere is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God
        of Elijah?\u201D And when he had struck the water, the water was parted to
        the one side and to the other, and Elisha went over.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now when the sons of the prophets who were at Jericho saw him opposite
        them, they said, \u201CThe spirit of Elijah rests on Elisha.\u201D And they
        came to meet him and bowed to the ground before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CBehold now, there are with your servants
        fifty strong men. Please let them go and seek your master. It may be that
        the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has caught him up and cast
        him upon some mountain or into some valley.\u201D And he said, \u201CYou
        shall not send.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But when they urged him till he was ashamed, he said, \u201CSend.\u201D
        They sent therefore fifty men. And for three days they sought him but did
        not find him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And they came back to him while he was staying at Jericho, and he
        said to them, \u201CDid I not say to you, \u2018Do not go\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now the men of the city said to Elisha, \u201CBehold, the situation
        of this city is pleasant, as my lord sees, but the water is bad, and the
        land is unfruitful.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He said, \u201CBring me a new bowl, and put salt in it.\u201D So
        they brought it to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then he went to the spring of water and threw salt in it and said,
        \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I have healed this water;
        from now on neither death nor miscarriage shall come from it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So the water has been healed to this day, according to the word that
        Elisha spoke.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He went up from there to Bethel, and while he was going up on the
        way, some small boys came out of the city and jeered at him, saying, \u201CGo
        up, you baldhead! Go up, you baldhead!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And he turned around, and when he saw them, he cursed them in the
        name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And two she-bears came out of the
        woods and tore forty-two of the boys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: From there he went on to Mount Carmel, and from there he returned
        to Samaria.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Moab Rebels Against Israel'
      title: Moab Rebels Against Israel
      number: 1
      content: '    In the eighteenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, Jehoram
        the son of Ahab became king over Israel in Samaria, and he reigned twelve
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        though not like his father and mother, for he put away the pillar of Baal
        that his father had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Nevertheless, he clung to the sin of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which
        he made Israel to sin; he did not depart from it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Mesha king of Moab was a sheep breeder, and he had to deliver
        to the king of Israel 100,000 lambs and the wool of 100,000 rams. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But when Ahab died, the king of Moab rebelled against the king of
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So King Jehoram marched out of Samaria at that time and mustered
        all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he went and sent word to Jehoshaphat king of Judah: \u201CThe
        king of Moab has rebelled against me. Will you go with me to battle against
        Moab?\u201D And he said, \u201CI will go. I am as you are, my people as your
        people, my horses as your horses.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he said, \u201CBy which way shall we march?\u201D Jehoram answered,
        \u201CBy the way of the wilderness of Edom.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the king of Israel went with the king of Judah and the king of
        Edom. And when they had made a circuitous march of seven days, there was
        no water for the army or for the animals that followed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the king of Israel said, \u201CAlas! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has called these three kings to give them into the hand of Moab.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Jehoshaphat said, \u201CIs there no prophet of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        here, through whom we may inquire of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201D
        Then one of the king of Israel\u2019s servants answered, \u201CElisha the
        son of Shaphat is here, who poured water on the hands of Elijah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Jehoshaphat said, \u201CThe word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is with him.\u201D So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat and the king of
        Edom went down to him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Elisha said to the king of Israel, \u201CWhat have I to do with
        you? Go to the prophets of your father and to the prophets of your mother.\u201D
        But the king of Israel said to him, \u201CNo; it is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        who has called these three kings to give them into the hand of Moab.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Elisha said, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts
        lives, before whom I stand, were it not that I have regard for Jehoshaphat
        the king of Judah, I would neither look at you nor see you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But now bring me a musician.\u201D And when the musician played,
        the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came upon him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he said, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018I
        will make this dry streambed full of pools.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018You shall not
        see wind or rain, but that streambed shall be filled with water, so that
        you shall drink, you, your livestock, and your animals.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'This is a light thing in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        He will also give the Moabites into your hand, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and you shall attack every fortified city and every choice city,
        and shall fell every good tree and stop up all springs of water and ruin
        every good piece of land with stones.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The next morning, about the time of offering the sacrifice, behold,
        water came from the direction of Edom, till the country was filled with water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When all the Moabites heard that the kings had come up to fight against
        them, all who were able to put on armor, from the youngest to the oldest,
        were called out and were drawn up at the border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And when they rose early in the morning and the sun shone on the
        water, the Moabites saw the water opposite them as red as blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And they said, \u201CThis is blood; the kings have surely fought
        together and struck one another down. Now then, Moab, to the spoil!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But when they came to the camp of Israel, the Israelites rose and
        struck the Moabites, till they fled before them. And they went forward, striking
        the Moabites as they went.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:24 '
        content: Septuagint; the meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And they overthrew the cities, and on every good piece of land every
        man threw a stone until it was covered. They stopped every spring of water
        and felled all the good trees, till only its stones were left in Kir-hareseth,
        and the slingers surrounded and attacked it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When the king of Moab saw that the battle was going against him,
        he took with him 700 swordsmen to break through, opposite the king of Edom,
        but they could not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Then he took his oldest son who was to reign in his place and offered
        him for a burnt offering on the wall. And there came great wrath against
        Israel. And they withdrew from him and returned to their own land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elisha and the Widow\u2019s Oil"
      title: "Elisha and the Widow\u2019s Oil"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the wife of one of the sons of the prophets cried to Elisha,
        \u201CYour servant my husband is dead, and you know that your servant feared
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, but the creditor has come to take my two
        children to be his slaves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Elisha said to her, \u201CWhat shall I do for you? Tell me; what
        have you in the house?\u201D And she said, \u201CYour servant has nothing
        in the house except a jar of oil.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said, \u201CGo outside, borrow vessels from all your neighbors,
        empty vessels and not too few. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then go in and shut the door behind yourself and your sons and pour
        into all these vessels. And when one is full, set it aside.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So she went from him and shut the door behind herself and her sons.
        And as she poured they brought the vessels to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When the vessels were full, she said to her son, \u201CBring me another
        vessel.\u201D And he said to her, \u201CThere is not another.\u201D Then
        the oil stopped flowing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Elisha and the Shunammite Woman'
      title: Elisha and the Shunammite Woman
      number: 7
      content: "She came and told the man of God, and he said, \u201CGo, sell the
        oil and pay your debts, and you and your sons can live on the rest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'One day Elisha went on to Shunem, where a wealthy woman lived, who
        urged him to eat some food. So whenever he passed that way, he would turn
        in there to eat food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And she said to her husband, \u201CBehold now, I know that this is
        a holy man of God who is continually passing our way. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Let us make a small room on the roof with walls and put there for
        him a bed, a table, a chair, and a lamp, so that whenever he comes to us,
        he can go in there.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'One day he came there, and he turned into the chamber and rested
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said to Gehazi his servant, \u201CCall this Shunammite.\u201D
        When he had called her, she stood before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CSay now to her, \u2018See, you have taken
        all this trouble for us; what is to be done for you? Would you have a word
        spoken on your behalf to the king or to the commander of the army?\u2019\u201D
        She answered, \u201CI dwell among my own people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhat then is to be done for her?\u201D Gehazi
        answered, \u201CWell, she has no son, and her husband is old.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He said, \u201CCall her.\u201D And when he had called her, she stood
        in the doorway. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he said, \u201CAt this season, about this time next year, you
        shall embrace a son.\u201D And she said, \u201CNo, my lord, O man of God;
        do not lie to your servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Elisha Raises the Shunammite\u2019s Son"
      title: "Elisha Raises the Shunammite\u2019s Son"
      number: 17
      content: 'But the woman conceived, and she bore a son about that time the following
        spring, as Elisha had said to her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When the child had grown, he went out one day to his father among
        the reapers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he said to his father, \u201COh, my head, my head!\u201D The
        father said to his servant, \u201CCarry him to his mother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And when he had lifted him and brought him to his mother, the child
        sat on her lap till noon, and then he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And she went up and laid him on the bed of the man of God and shut
        the door behind him and went out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then she called to her husband and said, \u201CSend me one of the
        servants and one of the donkeys, that I may quickly go to the man of God
        and come back again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhy will you go to him today? It is neither new
        moon nor Sabbath.\u201D She said, \u201CAll is well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then she saddled the donkey, and she said to her servant, \u201CUrge
        the animal on; do not slacken the pace for me unless I tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So she set out and came to the man of God at Mount Carmel.When the
        man of God saw her coming, he said to Gehazi his servant, \u201CLook, there
        is the Shunammite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Run at once to meet her and say to her, \u2018Is all well with you?
        Is all well with your husband? Is all well with the child?\u2019\u201D And
        she answered, \u201CAll is well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And when she came to the mountain to the man of God, she caught hold
        of his feet. And Gehazi came to push her away. But the man of God said, \u201CLeave
        her alone, for she is in bitter distress, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has hidden it from me and has not told me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then she said, \u201CDid I ask my lord for a son? Did I not say,
        \u2018Do not deceive me?\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "He said to Gehazi, \u201CTie up your garment and take my staff in
        your hand and go. If you meet anyone, do not greet him, and if anyone greets
        you, do not reply. And lay my staff on the face of the child.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then the mother of the child said, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.\u201D So he arose and
        followed her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Gehazi went on ahead and laid the staff on the face of the child,
        but there was no sound or sign of life. Therefore he returned to meet him
        and told him, \u201CThe child has not awakened.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When Elisha came into the house, he saw the child lying dead on his
        bed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So he went in and shut the door behind the two of them and prayed
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then he went up and lay on the child, putting his mouth on his mouth,
        his eyes on his eyes, and his hands on his hands. And as he stretched himself
        upon him, the flesh of the child became warm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then he got up again and walked once back and forth in the house,
        and went up and stretched himself upon him. The child sneezed seven times,
        and the child opened his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then he summoned Gehazi and said, \u201CCall this Shunammite.\u201D
        So he called her. And when she came to him, he said, \u201CPick up your son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: Elisha Purifies the Deadly Stew'
      title: Elisha Purifies the Deadly Stew
      number: 37
      content: 'She came and fell at his feet, bowing to the ground. Then she picked
        up her son and went out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Elisha came again to Gilgal when there was a famine in the land.
        And as the sons of the prophets were sitting before him, he said to his servant,
        \u201CSet on the large pot, and boil stew for the sons of the prophets.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'One of them went out into the field to gather herbs, and found a
        wild vine and gathered from it his lap full of wild gourds, and came and
        cut them up into the pot of stew, not knowing what they were. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And they poured out some for the men to eat. But while they were
        eating of the stew, they cried out, \u201CO man of God, there is death in
        the pot!\u201D And they could not eat it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "He said, \u201CThen bring flour.\u201D And he threw it into the pot
        and said, \u201CPour some out for the men, that they may eat.\u201D And there
        was no harm in the pot.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "A man came from Baal-shalishah, bringing the man of God bread of
        the firstfruits, twenty loaves of barley and fresh ears of grain in his sack.
        And Elisha said, \u201CGive to the men, that they may eat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "But his servant said, \u201CHow can I set this before a hundred men?\u201D
        So he repeated, \u201CGive them to the men, that they may eat, for thus says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018They shall eat and have some left.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: So he set it before them. And they ate and had some left, according
        to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Naaman Healed of Leprosy'
      title: Naaman Healed of Leprosy
      number: 1
      content: '    Naaman, commander of the army of the king of Syria, was a great
        man with his master and in high favor, because by him the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had given victory to Syria. He was a mighty man of valor, but he was a leper.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:1 '
        content: was a term for several skin diseases; see Leviticus 13
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now the Syrians on one of their raids had carried off a little girl
        from the land of Israel, and she worked in the service of Naaman\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "She said to her mistress, \u201CWould that my lord were with the
        prophet who is in Samaria! He would cure him of his leprosy.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Naaman went in and told his lord, \u201CThus and so spoke the
        girl from the land of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the king of Syria said, \u201CGo now, and I will send a letter
        to the king of Israel.\u201DSo he went, taking with him ten talents of silver,
        six thousand shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of gold, and ten changes of clothing. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms; a was about 2/5 ounce or
          11 grams
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he brought the letter to the king of Israel, which read, \u201CWhen
        this letter reaches you, know that I have sent to you Naaman my servant,
        that you may cure him of his leprosy.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And when the king of Israel read the letter, he tore his clothes
        and said, \u201CAm I God, to kill and to make alive, that this man sends
        word to me to cure a man of his leprosy? Only consider, and see how he is
        seeking a quarrel with me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But when Elisha the man of God heard that the king of Israel had
        torn his clothes, he sent to the king, saying, \u201CWhy have you torn your
        clothes? Let him come now to me, that he may know that there is a prophet
        in Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Naaman came with his horses and chariots and stood at the door
        of Elisha\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Elisha sent a messenger to him, saying, \u201CGo and wash in
        the Jordan seven times, and your flesh shall be restored, and you shall be
        clean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Naaman was angry and went away, saying, \u201CBehold, I thought
        that he would surely come out to me and stand and call upon the name of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> his God, and wave his hand over the place and
        cure the leper. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Are not Abana[[COMMENT(0)]] and Pharpar, the rivers of Damascus,
        better than all the waters of Israel? Could I not wash in them and be clean?\u201D
        So he turned and went away in a rage. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But his servants came near and said to him, \u201CMy father, it is
        a great word the prophet has spoken to you; will you not do it? Has he actually
        said to you, \u2018Wash, and be clean\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Gehazi\u2019s Greed and Punishment"
      title: "Gehazi\u2019s Greed and Punishment"
      number: 14
      content: 'So he went down and dipped himself seven times in the Jordan, according
        to the word of the man of God, and his flesh was restored like the flesh
        of a little child, and he was clean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then he returned to the man of God, he and all his company, and he
        came and stood before him. And he said, \u201CBehold, I know that there is
        no God in all the earth but in Israel; so accept now a present from your
        servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But he said, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, before
        whom I stand, I will receive none.\u201D And he urged him to take it, but
        he refused. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Naaman said, \u201CIf not, please let there be given to your
        servant two mule loads of earth, for from now on your servant will not offer
        burnt offering or sacrifice to any god but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "In this matter may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> pardon your servant:
        when my master goes into the house of Rimmon to worship there, leaning on
        my arm, and I bow myself in the house of Rimmon, when I bow myself in the
        house of Rimmon, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> pardon your servant in this
        matter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He said to him, \u201CGo in peace.\u201DBut when Naaman had gone
        from him a short distance, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Gehazi, the servant of Elisha the man of God, said, \u201CSee, my
        master has spared this Naaman the Syrian, in not accepting from his hand
        what he brought. As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, I will run after
        him and get something from him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So Gehazi followed Naaman. And when Naaman saw someone running after
        him, he got down from the chariot to meet him and said, \u201CIs all well?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And he said, \u201CAll is well. My master has sent me to say, \u2018There
        have just now come to me from the hill country of Ephraim two young men of
        the sons of the prophets. Please give them a talent of silver and two changes
        of clothing.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Naaman said, \u201CBe pleased to accept two talents.\u201D And
        he urged him and tied up two talents of silver in two bags, with two changes
        of clothing, and laid them on two of his servants. And they carried them
        before Gehazi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And when he came to the hill, he took them from their hand and put
        them in the house, and he sent the men away, and they departed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He went in and stood before his master, and Elisha said to him, \u201CWhere
        have you been, Gehazi?\u201D And he said, \u201CYour servant went nowhere.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But he said to him, \u201CDid not my heart go when the man turned
        from his chariot to meet you? Was it a time to accept money and garments,
        olive orchards and vineyards, sheep and oxen, male servants and female servants? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Therefore the leprosy of Naaman shall cling to you and to your descendants
        forever.\u201D So he went out from his presence a leper, like snow."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Axe Head Recovered'
      title: The Axe Head Recovered
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the sons of the prophets said to Elisha, \u201CSee, the place
        where we dwell under your charge is too small for us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Let us go to the Jordan and each of us get there a log, and let us
        make a place for us to dwell there.\u201D And he answered, \u201CGo.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then one of them said, \u201CBe pleased to go with your servants.\u201D
        And he answered, \u201CI will go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So he went with them. And when they came to the Jordan, they cut
        down trees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But as one was felling a log, his axe head fell into the water, and
        he cried out, \u201CAlas, my master! It was borrowed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the man of God said, \u201CWhere did it fall?\u201D When he
        showed him the place, he cut off a stick and threw it in there and made the
        iron float. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Horses and Chariots of Fire'
      title: Horses and Chariots of Fire
      number: 7
      content: "And he said, \u201CTake it up.\u201D So he reached out his hand and
        took it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Once when the king of Syria was warring against Israel, he took counsel
        with his servants, saying, \u201CAt such and such a place shall be my camp.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the man of God sent word to the king of Israel, \u201CBeware
        that you do not pass this place, for the Syrians are going down there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the king of Israel sent to the place about which the man of God
        told him. Thus he used to warn him, so that he saved himself there more than
        once or twice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the mind of the king of Syria was greatly troubled because of
        this thing, and he called his servants and said to them, \u201CWill you not
        show me who of us is for the king of Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And one of his servants said, \u201CNone, my lord, O king; but Elisha,
        the prophet who is in Israel, tells the king of Israel the words that you
        speak in your bedroom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he said, \u201CGo and see where he is, that I may send and seize
        him.\u201D It was told him, \u201CBehold, he is in Dothan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So he sent there horses and chariots and a great army, and they came
        by night and surrounded the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When the servant of the man of God rose early in the morning and
        went out, behold, an army with horses and chariots was all around the city.
        And the servant said, \u201CAlas, my master! What shall we do?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He said, \u201CDo not be afraid, for those who are with us are more
        than those who are with them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Elisha prayed and said, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        please open his eyes that he may see.\u201D So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        opened the eyes of the young man, and he saw, and behold, the mountain was
        full of horses and chariots of fire all around Elisha. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And when the Syrians came down against him, Elisha prayed to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said, \u201CPlease strike this people with
        blindness.\u201D So he struck them with blindness in accordance with the
        prayer of Elisha. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Elisha said to them, \u201CThis is not the way, and this is not
        the city. Follow me, and I will bring you to the man whom you seek.\u201D
        And he led them to Samaria.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "As soon as they entered Samaria, Elisha said, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        open the eyes of these men, that they may see.\u201D So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        opened their eyes and they saw, and behold, they were in the midst of Samaria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "As soon as the king of Israel saw them, he said to Elisha, \u201CMy
        father, shall I strike them down? Shall I strike them down?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He answered, \u201CYou shall not strike them down. Would you strike
        down those whom you have taken captive with your sword and with your bow?
        Set bread and water before them, that they may eat and drink and go to their
        master.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "23: Ben-hadad\u2019s Siege of Samaria"
      title: "Ben-hadad\u2019s Siege of Samaria"
      number: 23
      content: 'So he prepared for them a great feast, and when they had eaten and
        drunk, he sent them away, and they went to their master. And the Syrians
        did not come again on raids into the land of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Afterward Ben-hadad king of Syria mustered his entire army and went
        up and besieged Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And there was a great famine in Samaria, as they besieged it, until
        a donkey\u2019s head was sold for eighty shekels of silver, and the fourth
        part of a kab[[COMMENT(0)]] of dove\u2019s dung for five shekels of silver. "
      comments:
      - number: '6:25 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams; a was about 1 quart or 1 liter
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Now as the king of Israel was passing by on the wall, a woman cried
        out to him, saying, \u201CHelp, my lord, O king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he said, \u201CIf the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not help
        you, how shall I help you? From the threshing floor, or from the winepress?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And the king asked her, \u201CWhat is your trouble?\u201D She answered,
        \u201CThis woman said to me, \u2018Give your son, that we may eat him today,
        and we will eat my son tomorrow.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So we boiled my son and ate him. And on the next day I said to her,
        \u2018Give your son, that we may eat him.\u2019 But she has hidden her son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "When the king heard the words of the woman, he tore his clothes\u2014now
        he was passing by on the wall\u2014and the people looked, and behold, he
        had sackcloth beneath on his body\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "and he said, \u201CMay God do so to me and more also, if the head
        of Elisha the son of Shaphat remains on his shoulders today.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Elisha was sitting in his house, and the elders were sitting with
        him. Now the king had dispatched a man from his presence, but before the
        messenger arrived Elisha said to the elders, \u201CDo you see how this murderer
        has sent to take off my head? Look, when the messenger comes, shut the door
        and hold the door fast against him. Is not the sound of his master\u2019s
        feet behind him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And while he was still speaking with them, the messenger came down
        to him and said, \u201CThis trouble is from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!
        Why should I wait for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> any longer?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elisha Promises Food'
      title: Elisha Promises Food
      number: 1
      content: "  But Elisha said, \u201CHear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, Tomorrow about this time a seah[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of fine flour shall be sold for a shekel, and two seahs of barley for a shekel,
        at the gate of Samaria.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '7:1 '
        content: A was about 7 quarts or 7.3 litersA was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '2: The Syrians Flee'
      title: The Syrians Flee
      number: 2
      content: "Then the captain on whose hand the king leaned said to the man of
        God, \u201CIf the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> himself should make windows
        in heaven, could this thing be?\u201D But he said, \u201CYou shall see it
        with your own eyes, but you shall not eat of it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now there were four men who were lepers[[COMMENT(0)]]  at the entrance
        to the gate. And they said to one another, \u201CWhy are we sitting here
        until we die? "
      comments:
      - number: '7:3 '
        content: was a term for several skin diseases; see Leviticus 13
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "If we say, \u2018Let us enter the city,\u2019 the famine is in the
        city, and we shall die there. And if we sit here, we die also. So now come,
        let us go over to the camp of the Syrians. If they spare our lives we shall
        live, and if they kill us we shall but die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So they arose at twilight to go to the camp of the Syrians. But when
        they came to the edge of the camp of the Syrians, behold, there was no one
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the Lord had made the army of the Syrians hear the sound of chariots
        and of horses, the sound of a great army, so that they said to one another,
        \u201CBehold, the king of Israel has hired against us the kings of the Hittites
        and the kings of Egypt to come against us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So they fled away in the twilight and abandoned their tents, their
        horses, and their donkeys, leaving the camp as it was, and fled for their
        lives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And when these lepers came to the edge of the camp, they went into
        a tent and ate and drank, and they carried off silver and gold and clothing
        and went and hid them. Then they came back and entered another tent and carried
        off things from it and went and hid them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then they said to one another, \u201CWe are not doing right. This
        day is a day of good news. If we are silent and wait until the morning light,
        punishment will overtake us. Now therefore come; let us go and tell the king\u2019s
        household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So they came and called to the gatekeepers of the city and told them,
        \u201CWe came to the camp of the Syrians, and behold, there was no one to
        be seen or heard there, nothing but the horses tied and the donkeys tied
        and the tents as they were.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the gatekeepers called out, and it was told within the king\u2019s
        household. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the king rose in the night and said to his servants, \u201CI
        will tell you what the Syrians have done to us. They know that we are hungry.
        Therefore they have gone out of the camp to hide themselves in the open country,
        thinking, \u2018When they come out of the city, we shall take them alive
        and get into the city.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And one of his servants said, \u201CLet some men take five of the
        remaining horses, seeing that those who are left here will fare like the
        whole multitude of Israel who have already perished. Let us send and see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So they took two horsemen, and the king sent them after the army
        of the Syrians, saying, \u201CGo and see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So they went after them as far as the Jordan, and behold, all the
        way was littered with garments and equipment that the Syrians had thrown
        away in their haste. And the messengers returned and told the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the people went out and plundered the camp of the Syrians. So
        a seah of fine flour was sold for a shekel, and two seahs of barley for a
        shekel, according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now the king had appointed the captain on whose hand he leaned to
        have charge of the gate. And the people trampled him in the gate, so that
        he died, as the man of God had said when the king came down to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For when the man of God had said to the king, \u201CTwo seahs of
        barley shall be sold for a shekel, and a seah of fine flour for a shekel,
        about this time tomorrow in the gate of Samaria,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "the captain had answered the man of God, \u201CIf the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        himself should make windows in heaven, could such a thing be?\u201D And he
        had said, \u201CYou shall see it with your own eyes, but you shall not eat
        of it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And so it happened to him, for the people trampled him in the gate
        and he died.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Shunammite\u2019s Land Restored"
      title: "The Shunammite\u2019s Land Restored"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Elisha had said to the woman whose son he had restored to life,
        \u201CArise, and depart with your household, and sojourn wherever you can,
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  has called for a famine, and it will
        come upon the land for seven years.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the woman arose and did according to the word of the man of God.
        She went with her household and sojourned in the land of the Philistines
        seven years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And at the end of the seven years, when the woman returned from the
        land of the Philistines, she went to appeal to the king for her house and
        her land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now the king was talking with Gehazi the servant of the man of God,
        saying, \u201CTell me all the great things that Elisha has done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And while he was telling the king how Elisha had restored the dead
        to life, behold, the woman whose son he had restored to life appealed to
        the king for her house and her land. And Gehazi said, \u201CMy lord, O king,
        here is the woman, and here is her son whom Elisha restored to life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Hazael Murders Ben-hadad'
      title: Hazael Murders Ben-hadad
      number: 6
      content: "And when the king asked the woman, she told him. So the king appointed
        an official for her, saying, \u201CRestore all that was hers, together with
        all the produce of the fields from the day that she left the land until now.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now Elisha came to Damascus. Ben-hadad the king of Syria was sick.
        And when it was told him, \u201CThe man of God has come here,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "the king said to Hazael, \u201CTake a present with you and go to
        meet the man of God, and inquire of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> through
        him, saying, \u2018Shall I recover from this sickness?\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Hazael went to meet him, and took a present with him, all kinds
        of goods of Damascus, forty camels\u2019 loads. When he came and stood before
        him, he said, \u201CYour son Ben-hadad king of Syria has sent me to you,
        saying, \u2018Shall I recover from this sickness?\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Elisha said to him, \u201CGo, say to him, \u2018You shall certainly
        recover,\u2019 but[[COMMENT(0)]] the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has shown
        me that he shall certainly die.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '8:10 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he fixed his gaze and stared at him, until he was embarrassed.
        And the man of God wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Hazael said, \u201CWhy does my lord weep?\u201D He answered,
        \u201CBecause I know the evil that you will do to the people of Israel. You
        will set on fire their fortresses, and you will kill their young men with
        the sword and dash in pieces their little ones and rip open their pregnant
        women.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Hazael said, \u201CWhat is your servant, who is but a dog, that
        he should do this great thing?\u201D Elisha answered, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has shown me that you are to be king over Syria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he departed from Elisha and came to his master, who said to
        him, \u201CWhat did Elisha say to you?\u201D And he answered, \u201CHe told
        me that you would certainly recover.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Jehoram Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jehoram Reigns in Judah
      number: 15
      content: 'But the next day he took the bed cloth[[COMMENT(0)]] and dipped it
        in water and spread it over his face, till he died. And Hazael became king
        in his place.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:15 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In the fifth year of Joram the son of Ahab, king of Israel, when
        Jehoshaphat was king of Judah,[[COMMENT(0)]] Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat,
        king of Judah, began to reign. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:16 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac lack '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned eight
        years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he walked in the way of the kings of Israel, as the house of
        Ahab had done, for the daughter of Ahab was his wife. And he did what was
        evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Yet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was not willing to destroy Judah,
        for the sake of David his servant, since he promised to give a lamp to him
        and to his sons forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In his days Edom revolted from the rule of Judah and set up a king
        of their own. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Joram[[COMMENT(0)]] passed over to Zair with all his chariots
        and rose by night, and he and his chariot commanders struck the Edomites
        who had surrounded him, but his army fled home. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:21 '
        content: is an alternate spelling of (the son of Jehoshaphat) as in verse
          16; also verses 23, 24
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Edom revolted from the rule of Judah to this day. Then Libnah
        revolted at the same time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Joram, and all that he did, are they
        not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Ahaziah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Ahaziah Reigns in Judah
      number: 24
      content: 'So Joram slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in
        the city of David, and Ahaziah his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  In the twelfth year of Joram the son of Ahab, king of Israel, Ahaziah
        the son of Jehoram, king of Judah, began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Ahaziah was twenty-two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        one year in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Athaliah; she was a granddaughter
        of Omri king of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He also walked in the way of the house of Ahab and did what was evil
        in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, as the house of Ahab had
        done, for he was son-in-law to the house of Ahab.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He went with Joram the son of Ahab to make war against Hazael king
        of Syria at Ramoth-gilead, and the Syrians wounded Joram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: And King Joram returned to be healed in Jezreel of the wounds that
        the Syrians had given him at Ramah, when he fought against Hazael king of
        Syria. And Ahaziah the son of Jehoram king of Judah went down to see Joram
        the son of Ahab in Jezreel, because he was sick.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehu Anointed King of Israel'
      title: Jehu Anointed King of Israel
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Elisha the prophet called one of the sons of the prophets
        and said to him, \u201CTie up your garments, and take this flask of oil in
        your hand, and go to Ramoth-gilead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when you arrive, look there for Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat,
        son of Nimshi. And go in and have him rise from among his fellows, and lead
        him to an inner chamber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then take the flask of oil and pour it on his head and say, \u2018Thus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I anoint you king over Israel.\u2019
        Then open the door and flee; do not linger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the young man, the servant of the prophet, went to Ramoth-gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And when he came, behold, the commanders of the army were in council.
        And he said, \u201CI have a word for you, O commander.\u201D And Jehu said,
        \u201CTo which of us all?\u201D And he said, \u201CTo you, O commander.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So he arose and went into the house. And the young man poured the
        oil on his head, saying to him, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, I anoint you king over the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        over Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And you shall strike down the house of Ahab your master, so that
        I may avenge on Jezebel the blood of my servants the prophets, and the blood
        of all the servants of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the whole house of Ahab shall perish, and I will cut off from
        Ahab every male, bond or free, in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I will make the house of Ahab like the house of Jeroboam the
        son of Nebat, and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the dogs shall eat Jezebel in the territory of Jezreel, and none
        shall bury her.\u201D Then he opened the door and fled.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When Jehu came out to the servants of his master, they said to him,
        \u201CIs all well? Why did this mad fellow come to you?\u201D And he said
        to them, \u201CYou know the fellow and his talk.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they said, \u201CThat is not true; tell us now.\u201D And he
        said, \u201CThus and so he spoke to me, saying, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        I anoint you king over Israel.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jehu Assassinates Joram and Ahaziah'
      title: Jehu Assassinates Joram and Ahaziah
      number: 13
      content: "Then in haste every man of them took his garment and put it under
        him on the bare[[COMMENT(0)]] steps, and they blew the trumpet and proclaimed,
        \u201CJehu is king.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:13 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Thus Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat the son of Nimshi conspired against
        Joram. (Now Joram with all Israel had been on guard at Ramoth-gilead against
        Hazael king of Syria, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "but King Joram had returned to be healed in Jezreel of the wounds
        that the Syrians had given him, when he fought with Hazael king of Syria.)
        So Jehu said, \u201CIf this is your decision, then let no one slip out of
        the city to go and tell the news in Jezreel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Jehu mounted his chariot and went to Jezreel, for Joram lay
        there. And Ahaziah king of Judah had come down to visit Joram.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now the watchman was standing on the tower in Jezreel, and he saw
        the company of Jehu as he came and said, \u201CI see a company.\u201D And
        Joram said, \u201CTake a horseman and send to meet them, and let him say,
        \u2018Is it peace?\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So a man on horseback went to meet him and said, \u201CThus says
        the king, \u2018Is it peace?\u2019\u201D And Jehu said, \u201CWhat do you
        have to do with peace? Turn around and ride behind me.\u201D And the watchman
        reported, saying, \u201CThe messenger reached them, but he is not coming
        back.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he sent out a second horseman, who came to them and said, \u201CThus
        the king has said, \u2018Is it peace?\u2019\u201D And Jehu answered, \u201CWhat
        do you have to do with peace? Turn around and ride behind me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Again the watchman reported, \u201CHe reached them, but he is not
        coming back. And the driving is like the driving of Jehu the son of Nimshi,
        for he drives furiously.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Joram said, \u201CMake ready.\u201D And they made ready his chariot.
        Then Joram king of Israel and Ahaziah king of Judah set out, each in his
        chariot, and went to meet Jehu, and met him at the property of Naboth the
        Jezreelite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And when Joram saw Jehu, he said, \u201CIs it peace, Jehu?\u201D
        He answered, \u201CWhat peace can there be, so long as the whorings and the
        sorceries of your mother Jezebel are so many?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Joram reined about and fled, saying to Ahaziah, \u201CTreachery,
        O Ahaziah!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Jehu drew his bow with his full strength, and shot Joram between
        the shoulders, so that the arrow pierced his heart, and he sank in his chariot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jehu said to Bidkar his aide, \u201CTake him up and throw him on
        the plot of ground belonging to Naboth the Jezreelite. For remember, when
        you and I rode side by side behind Ahab his father, how the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        made this pronouncement against him: "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u2018As surely as I saw yesterday the blood of Naboth and the blood
        of his sons\u2014declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014I will repay
        you on this plot of ground.\u2019 Now therefore take him up and throw him
        on the plot of ground, in accordance with the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  When Ahaziah the king of Judah saw this, he fled in the direction
        of Beth-haggan. And Jehu pursued him and said, \u201CShoot him also.\u201D
        And they shot him[[COMMENT(0)]] in the chariot at the ascent of Gur, which
        is by Ibleam. And he fled to Megiddo and died there. "
      comments:
      - number: '9:27 '
        content: 'Syriac, Vulgate (compare Septuagint); Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'His servants carried him in a chariot to Jerusalem, and buried him
        in his tomb with his fathers in the city of David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Jehu Executes Jezebel'
      title: Jehu Executes Jezebel
      number: 29
      content: 'In the eleventh year of Joram the son of Ahab, Ahaziah began to reign
        over Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'When Jehu came to Jezreel, Jezebel heard of it. And she painted her
        eyes and adorned her head and looked out of the window. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And as Jehu entered the gate, she said, \u201CIs it peace, you Zimri,
        murderer of your master?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And he lifted up his face to the window and said, \u201CWho is on
        my side? Who?\u201D Two or three eunuchs looked out at him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "He said, \u201CThrow her down.\u201D So they threw her down. And
        some of her blood spattered on the wall and on the horses, and they trampled
        on her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then he went in and ate and drank. And he said, \u201CSee now to
        this cursed woman and bury her, for she is a king\u2019s daughter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'But when they went to bury her, they found no more of her than the
        skull and the feet and the palms of her hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "When they came back and told him, he said, \u201CThis is the word
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, which he spoke by his servant Elijah
        the Tishbite: \u2018In the territory of Jezreel the dogs shall eat the flesh
        of Jezebel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "and the corpse of Jezebel shall be as dung on the face of the field
        in the territory of Jezreel, so that no one can say, This is Jezebel.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jehu Slaughters Ahab\u2019s Descendants"
      title: "Jehu Slaughters Ahab\u2019s Descendants"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Ahab had seventy sons in Samaria. So Jehu wrote letters and
        sent them to Samaria, to the rulers of the city,[[COMMENT(0)]] to the elders,
        and to the guardians of the sons of Ahab, saying, '
      comments:
      - number: '10:1 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CNow then, as soon as this letter comes to you, seeing your
        master\u2019s sons are with you, and there are with you chariots and horses,
        fortified cities also, and weapons, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "select the best and fittest of your master\u2019s sons and set him
        on his father\u2019s throne and fight for your master\u2019s house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But they were exceedingly afraid and said, \u201CBehold, the two
        kings could not stand before him. How then can we stand?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So he who was over the palace, and he who was over the city, together
        with the elders and the guardians, sent to Jehu, saying, \u201CWe are your
        servants, and we will do all that you tell us. We will not make anyone king.
        Do whatever is good in your eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then he wrote to them a second letter, saying, \u201CIf you are on
        my side, and if you are ready to obey me, take the heads of your master\u2019s
        sons and come to me at Jezreel tomorrow at this time.\u201D Now the king\u2019s
        sons, seventy persons, were with the great men of the city, who were bringing
        them up. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And as soon as the letter came to them, they took the king\u2019s
        sons and slaughtered them, seventy persons, and put their heads in baskets
        and sent them to him at Jezreel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When the messenger came and told him, \u201CThey have brought the
        heads of the king\u2019s sons,\u201D he said, \u201CLay them in two heaps
        at the entrance of the gate until the morning.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then in the morning, when he went out, he stood and said to all the
        people, \u201CYou are innocent. It was I who conspired against my master
        and killed him, but who struck down all these? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Know then that there shall fall to the earth nothing of the word
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        spoke concerning the house of Ahab, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        done what he said by his servant Elijah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Jehu struck down all who remained of the house of Ahab in Jezreel,
        all his great men and his close friends and his priests, until he left him
        none remaining.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then he set out and went to Samaria. On the way, when he was at Beth-eked
        of the Shepherds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jehu met the relatives of Ahaziah king of Judah, and he said, \u201CWho
        are you?\u201D And they answered, \u201CWe are the relatives of Ahaziah,
        and we came down to visit the royal princes and the sons of the queen mother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He said, \u201CTake them alive.\u201D And they took them alive and
        slaughtered them at the pit of Beth-eked, forty-two persons, and he spared
        none of them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when he departed from there, he met Jehonadab the son of Rechab
        coming to meet him. And he greeted him and said to him, \u201CIs your heart
        true to my heart as mine is to yours?\u201D And Jehonadab answered, \u201CIt
        is.\u201D Jehu said,[[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CIf it is, give me your hand.\u201D
        So he gave him his hand. And Jehu took him up with him into the chariot. "
      comments:
      - number: '10:15 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he said, \u201CCome with me, and see my zeal for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D
        So he[[COMMENT(0)]] had him ride in his chariot. "
      comments:
      - number: '10:16 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac, Targum; Hebrew '
    - name: '17: Jehu Strikes Down the Prophets of Baal'
      title: Jehu Strikes Down the Prophets of Baal
      number: 17
      content: 'And when he came to Samaria, he struck down all who remained to Ahab
        in Samaria, till he had wiped them out, according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        that he spoke to Elijah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Jehu assembled all the people and said to them, \u201CAhab served
        Baal a little, but Jehu will serve him much. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now therefore call to me all the prophets of Baal, all his worshipers
        and all his priests. Let none be missing, for I have a great sacrifice to
        offer to Baal. Whoever is missing shall not live.\u201D But Jehu did it with
        cunning in order to destroy the worshipers of Baal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Jehu ordered, \u201CSanctify a solemn assembly for Baal.\u201D
        So they proclaimed it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Jehu sent throughout all Israel, and all the worshipers of Baal
        came, so that there was not a man left who did not come. And they entered
        the house of Baal, and the house of Baal was filled from one end to the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He said to him who was in charge of the wardrobe, \u201CBring out
        the vestments for all the worshipers of Baal.\u201D So he brought out the
        vestments for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Jehu went into the house of Baal with Jehonadab the son of Rechab,
        and he said to the worshipers of Baal, \u201CSearch, and see that there is
        no servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> here among you, but only the
        worshipers of Baal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then they[[COMMENT(0)]] went in to offer sacrifices and burnt offerings.Now
        Jehu had stationed eighty men outside and said, \u201CThe man who allows
        any of those whom I give into your hands to escape shall forfeit his life.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '10:24 '
        content: Septuagint (compare verse 25)
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So as soon as he had made an end of offering the burnt offering,
        Jehu said to the guard and to the officers, \u201CGo in and strike them down;
        let not a man escape.\u201D So when they put them to the sword, the guard
        and the officers cast them out and went into the inner room of the house
        of Baal, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and they brought out the pillar that was in the house of Baal and
        burned it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Jehu Reigns in Israel'
      title: Jehu Reigns in Israel
      number: 27
      content: 'And they demolished the pillar of Baal, and demolished the house
        of Baal, and made it a latrine to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Thus Jehu wiped out Baal from Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "But Jehu did not turn aside from the sins of Jeroboam the son of
        Nebat, which he made Israel to sin\u2014that is, the golden calves that were
        in Bethel and in Dan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Jehu, \u201CBecause you
        have done well in carrying out what is right in my eyes, and have done to
        the house of Ahab according to all that was in my heart, your sons of the
        fourth generation shall sit on the throne of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'But Jehu was not careful to walk in the law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, with all his heart. He did not turn from the sins of Jeroboam,
        which he made Israel to sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'In those days the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  began to cut off parts
        of Israel. Hazael defeated them throughout the territory of Israel: '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'from the Jordan eastward, all the land of Gilead, the Gadites, and
        the Reubenites, and the Manassites, from Aroer, which is by the Valley of
        the Arnon, that is, Gilead and Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehu and all that he did, and all his
        might, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of
        Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So Jehu slept with his fathers, and they buried him in Samaria. And
        Jehoahaz his son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: The time that Jehu reigned over Israel in Samaria was twenty-eight
        years.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Athaliah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Athaliah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '    Now when Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was
        dead, she arose and destroyed all the royal family. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Jehosheba, the daughter of King Joram, sister of Ahaziah, took
        Joash the son of Ahaziah and stole him away from among the king\u2019s sons
        who were being put to death, and she put[[COMMENT(0)]] him and his nurse
        in a bedroom. Thus they hid him from Athaliah, so that he was not put to
        death. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:2 '
        content: 'Compare 2 Chronicles 22:11; Hebrew lacks Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate
          (compare 2 Chronicles 22:11) '
    - name: '3: Joash Anointed King in Judah'
      title: Joash Anointed King in Judah
      number: 3
      content: 'And he remained with her six years, hidden in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        while Athaliah reigned over the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  But in the seventh year Jehoiada sent and brought the captains
        of the Carites and of the guards, and had them come to him in the house of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And he made a covenant with them and put
        them under oath in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and he showed
        them the king\u2019s son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he commanded them, \u201CThis is the thing that you shall do:
        one third of you, those who come off duty on the Sabbath and guard the king\u2019s
        house "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(another third being at the gate Sur and a third at the gate behind
        the guards) shall guard the palace.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:6 '
        content: 'The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain  '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the two divisions of you, which come on duty in force on the
        Sabbath and guard the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on behalf
        of the king, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "shall surround the king, each with his weapons in his hand. And whoever
        approaches the ranks is to be put to death. Be with the king when he goes
        out and when he comes in.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The captains did according to all that Jehoiada the priest commanded,
        and they each brought his men who were to go off duty on the Sabbath, with
        those who were to come on duty on the Sabbath, and came to Jehoiada the priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the priest gave to the captains the spears and shields that had
        been King David\u2019s, which were in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the guards stood, every man with his weapons in his hand, from
        the south side of the house to the north side of the house, around the altar
        and the house on behalf of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then he brought out the king\u2019s son and put the crown on him
        and gave him the testimony. And they proclaimed him king and anointed him,
        and they clapped their hands and said, \u201CLong live the king!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When Athaliah heard the noise of the guard and of the people, she
        went into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And when she looked, there was the king standing by the pillar, according
        to the custom, and the captains and the trumpeters beside the king, and all
        the people of the land rejoicing and blowing trumpets. And Athaliah tore
        her clothes and cried, \u201CTreason! Treason!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Jehoiada the priest commanded the captains who were set over
        the army, \u201CBring her out between the ranks, and put to death with the
        sword anyone who follows her.\u201D For the priest said, \u201CLet her not
        be put to death in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So they laid hands on her; and she went through the horses\u2019
        entrance to the king\u2019s house, and there she was put to death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Jehoiada made a covenant between the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and the king and people, that they should be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        people, and also between the king and the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then all the people of the land went to the house of Baal and tore
        it down; his altars and his images they broke in pieces, and they killed
        Mattan the priest of Baal before the altars. And the priest posted watchmen
        over the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he took the captains, the Carites, the guards, and all the people
        of the land, and they brought the king down from the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        marching through the gate of the guards to the king\u2019s house. And he
        took his seat on the throne of the kings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Jehoash Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jehoash Reigns in Judah
      number: 20
      content: "So all the people of the land rejoiced, and the city was quiet after
        Athaliah had been put to death with the sword at the king\u2019s house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]  Jehoash was seven years old when he began to reign.'
      comments:
      - number: '11:21 '
        content: '  Ch 12:1 in Hebrew  is an alternate spelling of (son of Ahaziah)
          as in verse 2'
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  In the seventh year of Jehu, Jehoash[[COMMENT(0)]] began to reign,
        and he reigned forty years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Zibiah
        of Beersheba. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:1 '
        content: is an alternate spelling of (son of Ahaziah) as in 11:2; also verses
          2, 4, 6, 7, 18
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Jehoash did what was right in the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        all his days, because Jehoiada the priest instructed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Jehoash Repairs the Temple'
      title: Jehoash Repairs the Temple
      number: 3
      content: 'Nevertheless, the high places were not taken away; the people continued
        to sacrifice and make offerings on the high places.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jehoash said to the priests, \u201CAll the money of the holy things
        that is brought into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the money
        for which each man is assessed\u2014the money from the assessment of persons\u2014and
        the money that a man\u2019s heart prompts him to bring into the house of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "let the priests take, each from his donor, and let them repair the
        house wherever any need of repairs is discovered.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But by the twenty-third year of King Jehoash, the priests had made
        no repairs on the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore King Jehoash summoned Jehoiada the priest and the other
        priests and said to them, \u201CWhy are you not repairing the house? Now
        therefore take no more money from your donors, but hand it over for the repair
        of the house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the priests agreed that they should take no more money from the
        people, and that they should not repair the house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Jehoiada the priest took a chest and bored a hole in the lid
        of it and set it beside the altar on the right side as one entered the house
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And the priests who guarded the threshold
        put in it all the money that was brought into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And whenever they saw that there was much money in the chest, the
        king\u2019s secretary and the high priest came up and they bagged and counted
        the money that was found in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then they would give the money that was weighed out into the hands
        of the workmen who had the oversight of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        And they paid it out to the carpenters and the builders who worked on the
        house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and to the masons and the stonecutters, as well as to buy timber
        and quarried stone for making repairs on the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and for any outlay for the repairs of the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But there were not made for the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        basins of silver, snuffers, bowls, trumpets, or any vessels of gold, or of
        silver, from the money that was brought into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'for that was given to the workmen who were repairing the house of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they did not ask for an accounting from the men into whose hand
        they delivered the money to pay out to the workmen, for they dealt honestly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The money from the guilt offerings and the money from the sin offerings
        was not brought into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; it belonged
        to the priests.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'At that time Hazael king of Syria went up and fought against Gath
        and took it. But when Hazael set his face to go up against Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Death of Joash'
      title: The Death of Joash
      number: 18
      content: "Jehoash king of Judah took all the sacred gifts that Jehoshaphat
        and Jehoram and Ahaziah his fathers, the kings of Judah, had dedicated, and
        his own sacred gifts, and all the gold that was found in the treasuries of
        the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and of the king\u2019s house,
        and sent these to Hazael king of Syria. Then Hazael went away from Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Joash and all that he did, are they not
        written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'His servants arose and made a conspiracy and struck down Joash in
        the house of Millo, on the way that goes down to Silla. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: It was Jozacar the son of Shimeath and Jehozabad the son of Shomer,
        his servants, who struck him down, so that he died. And they buried him with
        his fathers in the city of David, and Amaziah his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoahaz Reigns in Israel'
      title: Jehoahaz Reigns in Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  In the twenty-third year of Joash the son of Ahaziah, king of Judah,
        Jehoahaz the son of Jehu began to reign over Israel in Samaria, and he reigned
        seventeen years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and followed the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which he made Israel
        to sin; he did not depart from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was kindled against
        Israel, and he gave them continually into the hand of Hazael king of Syria
        and into the hand of Ben-hadad the son of Hazael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Jehoahaz sought the favor of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> listened to him, for he saw the oppression
        of Israel, how the king of Syria oppressed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '(Therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Israel a savior,
        so that they escaped from the hand of the Syrians, and the people of Israel
        lived in their homes as formerly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Nevertheless, they did not depart from the sins of the house of Jeroboam,
        which he made Israel to sin, but walked[[COMMENT(0)]] in them; and the Asherah
        also remained in Samaria.) '
      comments:
      - number: '13:6 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac, Targum, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For there was not left to Jehoahaz an army of more than fifty horsemen
        and ten chariots and ten thousand footmen, for the king of Syria had destroyed
        them and made them like the dust at threshing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoahaz and all that he did, and his
        might, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of
        Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Jehoash Reigns in Israel'
      title: Jehoash Reigns in Israel
      number: 9
      content: 'So Jehoahaz slept with his fathers, and they buried him in Samaria,
        and Joash his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In the thirty-seventh year of Joash king of Judah, Jehoash[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the son of Jehoahaz began to reign over Israel in Samaria, and he reigned
        sixteen years. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:10 '
        content: "is an alternate spelling of (son of Jehoahaz) as in verses 9, 12\u201314;
          also verse 25"
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He also did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        He did not depart from all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which he
        made Israel to sin, but he walked in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Joash and all that he did, and the might
        with which he fought against Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written
        in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Death of Elisha'
      title: The Death of Elisha
      number: 13
      content: 'So Joash slept with his fathers, and Jeroboam sat on his throne.
        And Joash was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now when Elisha had fallen sick with the illness of which he was
        to die, Joash king of Israel went down to him and wept before him, crying,
        \u201CMy father, my father! The chariots of Israel and its horsemen!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Elisha said to him, \u201CTake a bow and arrows.\u201D So he
        took a bow and arrows. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he said to the king of Israel, \u201CDraw the bow,\u201D and
        he drew it. And Elisha laid his hands on the king\u2019s hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said, \u201COpen the window eastward,\u201D and he opened
        it. Then Elisha said, \u201CShoot,\u201D and he shot. And he said, \u201CThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s arrow of victory, the arrow of victory
        over Syria! For you shall fight the Syrians in Aphek until you have made
        an end of them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said, \u201CTake the arrows,\u201D and he took them. And he
        said to the king of Israel, \u201CStrike the ground with them.\u201D And
        he struck three times and stopped. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the man of God was angry with him and said, \u201CYou should
        have struck five or six times; then you would have struck down Syria until
        you had made an end of it, but now you will strike down Syria only three
        times.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Elisha died, and they buried him. Now bands of Moabites used to
        invade the land in the spring of the year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And as a man was being buried, behold, a marauding band was seen
        and the man was thrown into the grave of Elisha, and as soon as the man touched
        the bones of Elisha, he revived and stood on his feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Now Hazael king of Syria oppressed Israel all the days of Jehoahaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was gracious to them and had
        compassion on them, and he turned toward them, because of his covenant with
        Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, and would not destroy them, nor has he cast them
        from his presence until now.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Hazael king of Syria died, Ben-hadad his son became king in
        his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Then Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz took again from Ben-hadad the son
        of Hazael the cities that he had taken from Jehoahaz his father in war. Three
        times Joash defeated him and recovered the cities of Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Amaziah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Amaziah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '    In the second year of Joash the son of Joahaz, king of Israel,
        Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jehoaddin of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he did what was right in the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        yet not like David his father. He did in all things as Joash his father had
        done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the high places were not removed; the people still sacrificed
        and made offerings on the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And as soon as the royal power was firmly in his hand, he struck
        down his servants who had struck down the king his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But he did not put to death the children of the murderers, according
        to what is written in the Book of the Law of Moses, where the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded, \u201CFathers shall not be put to death because of their children,
        nor shall children be put to death because of their fathers. But each one
        shall die for his own sin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  He struck down ten thousand Edomites in the Valley of Salt and
        took Sela by storm, and called it Joktheel, which is its name to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  Then Amaziah sent messengers to Jehoash[[COMMENT(0)]] the son of
        Jehoahaz, son of Jehu, king of Israel, saying, \u201CCome, let us look one
        another in the face.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '14:8 '
        content: "is an alternate spelling of (son of Jehoahaz) as in 13:9, 12\u201314;
          also verses 9, 11\u201316"
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Jehoash king of Israel sent word to Amaziah king of Judah, \u201CA
        thistle on Lebanon sent to a cedar on Lebanon, saying, \u2018Give your daughter
        to my son for a wife,\u2019 and a wild beast of Lebanon passed by and trampled
        down the thistle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You have indeed struck down Edom, and your heart has lifted you up.
        Be content with your glory, and stay at home, for why should you provoke
        trouble so that you fall, you and Judah with you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But Amaziah would not listen. So Jehoash king of Israel went up,
        and he and Amaziah king of Judah faced one another in battle at Beth-shemesh,
        which belongs to Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Judah was defeated by Israel, and every man fled to his home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Jehoash king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son
        of Jehoash, son of Ahaziah, at Beth-shemesh, and came to Jerusalem and broke
        down the wall of Jerusalem for four hundred cubits,[[COMMENT(0)]] from the
        Ephraim Gate to the Corner Gate. '
      comments:
      - number: '14:13 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he seized all the gold and silver, and all the vessels that were
        found in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and in the treasuries
        of the king\u2019s house, also hostages, and he returned to Samaria.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Now the rest of the acts of Jehoash that he did, and his might,
        and how he fought with Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written in the
        Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Jehoash slept with his fathers and was buried in Samaria with
        the kings of Israel, and Jeroboam his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, lived fifteen years after
        the death of Jehoash son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the rest of the deeds of Amaziah, are they not written in the
        Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And they made a conspiracy against him in Jerusalem, and he fled
        to Lachish. But they sent after him to Lachish and put him to death there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And they brought him on horses; and he was buried in Jerusalem with
        his fathers in the city of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And all the people of Judah took Azariah, who was sixteen years old,
        and made him king instead of his father Amaziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Jeroboam II Reigns in Israel'
      title: Jeroboam II Reigns in Israel
      number: 22
      content: 'He built Elath and restored it to Judah, after the king slept with
        his fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the fifteenth year of Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah,
        Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel, began to reign in Samaria, and
        he reigned forty-one years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        He did not depart from all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which he
        made Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He restored the border of Israel from Lebo-hamath as far as the Sea
        of the Arabah, according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, which he spoke by his servant Jonah the son of Amittai,
        the prophet, who was from Gath-hepher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  saw that the affliction of Israel
        was very bitter, for there was none left, bond or free, and there was none
        to help Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had not said that he would blot
        out the name of Israel from under heaven, so he saved them by the hand of
        Jeroboam the son of Joash.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jeroboam and all that he did, and his
        might, how he fought, and how he restored Damascus and Hamath to Judah in
        Israel, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of
        Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: And Jeroboam slept with his fathers, the kings of Israel, and Zechariah
        his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Azariah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Azariah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '    In the twenty-seventh year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Azariah
        the son of Amaziah, king of Judah, began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He was sixteen years old when he began to reign, and he reigned fifty-two
        years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jecoliah of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he did what was right in the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        according to all that his father Amaziah had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Nevertheless, the high places were not taken away. The people still
        sacrificed and made offerings on the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> touched the king, so that he
        was a leper[[COMMENT(0)]] to the day of his death, and he lived in a separate
        house. And Jotham the king\u2019s son was over the household, governing the
        people of the land. "
      comments:
      - number: '15:5 '
        content: was a term for several skin diseases; see Leviticus 13The meaning
          of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Azariah, and all that he did, are they
        not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Zechariah Reigns in Israel'
      title: Zechariah Reigns in Israel
      number: 7
      content: 'And Azariah slept with his fathers, and they buried him with his
        fathers in the city of David, and Jotham his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the thirty-eighth year of Azariah king of Judah, Zechariah the
        son of Jeroboam reigned over Israel in Samaria six months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        as his fathers had done. He did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam the
        son of Nebat, which he made Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Shallum the son of Jabesh conspired against him and struck him down
        at Ibleam and put him to death and reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now the rest of the deeds of Zechariah, behold, they are written
        in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Shallum Reigns in Israel'
      title: Shallum Reigns in Israel
      number: 12
      content: "(This was the promise of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he
        gave to Jehu, \u201CYour sons shall sit on the throne of Israel to the fourth
        generation.\u201D And so it came to pass.)  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Shallum the son of Jabesh began to reign in the thirty-ninth year
        of Uzziah[[COMMENT(0)]] king of Judah, and he reigned one month in Samaria. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:13 '
        content: 'Another name for '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Menahem the son of Gadi came up from Tirzah and came to Samaria,
        and he struck down Shallum the son of Jabesh in Samaria and put him to death
        and reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the rest of the deeds of Shallum, and the conspiracy that he
        made, behold, they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Menahem Reigns in Israel'
      title: Menahem Reigns in Israel
      number: 16
      content: 'At that time Menahem sacked Tiphsah and all who were in it and its
        territory from Tirzah on, because they did not open it to him. Therefore
        he sacked it, and he ripped open all the women in it who were pregnant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In the thirty-ninth year of Azariah king of Judah, Menahem the son
        of Gadi began to reign over Israel, and he reigned ten years in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        He did not depart all his days from all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat,
        which he made Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Pul[[COMMENT(0)]] the king of Assyria came against the land, and
        Menahem gave Pul a thousand talents of silver, that he might help him to
        confirm his hold on the royal power. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:19 '
        content: Another name for (compare verse 29)A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Menahem exacted the money from Israel, that is, from all the wealthy
        men, fifty shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver from every man, to give to the
        king of Assyria. So the king of Assyria turned back and did not stay there
        in the land. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:20 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now the rest of the deeds of Menahem and all that he did, are they
        not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Pekahiah Reigns in Israel'
      title: Pekahiah Reigns in Israel
      number: 22
      content: 'And Menahem slept with his fathers, and Pekahiah his son reigned
        in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the fiftieth year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekahiah the son of
        Menahem began to reign over Israel in Samaria, and he reigned two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        He did not turn away from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which he
        made Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Pekah the son of Remaliah, his captain, conspired against him
        with fifty men of the people of Gilead, and struck him down in Samaria, in
        the citadel of the king\u2019s house with Argob and Arieh; he put him to
        death and reigned in his place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Pekah Reigns in Israel'
      title: Pekah Reigns in Israel
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the rest of the deeds of Pekahiah and all that he did, behold,
        they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'In the fifty-second year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekah the son
        of Remaliah began to reign over Israel in Samaria, and he reigned twenty
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        He did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which he made
        Israel to sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'In the days of Pekah king of Israel, Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria
        came and captured Ijon, Abel-beth-maacah, Janoah, Kedesh, Hazor, Gilead,
        and Galilee, all the land of Naphtali, and he carried the people captive
        to Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Hoshea the son of Elah made a conspiracy against Pekah the son
        of Remaliah and struck him down and put him to death and reigned in his place,
        in the twentieth year of Jotham the son of Uzziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Jotham Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jotham Reigns in Judah
      number: 31
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Pekah and all that he did, behold, they
        are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'In the second year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, king of Israel,
        Jotham the son of Uzziah, king of Judah, began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "He was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jerusha the daughter
        of Zadok. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And he did what was right in the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        according to all that his father Uzziah had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Nevertheless, the high places were not removed. The people still
        sacrificed and made offerings on the high places. He built the upper gate
        of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jotham and all that he did, are they
        not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'In those days the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> began to send Rezin
        the king of Syria and Pekah the son of Remaliah against Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: Jotham slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the
        city of David his father, and Ahaz his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahaz Reigns in Judah'
      title: Ahaz Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  In the seventeenth year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, Ahaz the
        son of Jotham, king of Judah, began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Ahaz was twenty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        sixteen years in Jerusalem. And he did not do what was right in the eyes
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> his God, as his father David had done, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'but he walked in the way of the kings of Israel. He even burned his
        son as an offering,[[COMMENT(0)]]  according to the despicable practices
        of the nations whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> drove out before the
        people of Israel. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he sacrificed and made offerings on the high places and on the
        hills and under every green tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Then Rezin king of Syria and Pekah the son of Remaliah, king of
        Israel, came up to wage war on Jerusalem, and they besieged Ahaz but could
        not conquer him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'At that time Rezin the king of Syria recovered Elath for Syria and
        drove the men of Judah from Elath, and the Edomites came to Elath, where
        they dwell to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Ahaz sent messengers to Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria, saying,
        \u201CI am your servant and your son. Come up and rescue me from the hand
        of the king of Syria and from the hand of the king of Israel, who are attacking
        me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Ahaz also took the silver and gold that was found in the house of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and in the treasures of the king\u2019s house
        and sent a present to the king of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the king of Assyria listened to him. The king of Assyria marched
        up against Damascus and took it, carrying its people captive to Kir, and
        he killed Rezin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When King Ahaz went to Damascus to meet Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria,
        he saw the altar that was at Damascus. And King Ahaz sent to Uriah the priest
        a model of the altar, and its pattern, exact in all its details. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Uriah the priest built the altar; in accordance with all that
        King Ahaz had sent from Damascus, so Uriah the priest made it, before King
        Ahaz arrived from Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And when the king came from Damascus, the king viewed the altar.
        Then the king drew near to the altar and went up on it '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and burned his burnt offering and his grain offering and poured his
        drink offering and threw the blood of his peace offerings on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the bronze altar that was before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        he removed from the front of the house, from the place between his altar
        and the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and put it on the north
        side of his altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And King Ahaz commanded Uriah the priest, saying, \u201COn the great
        altar burn the morning burnt offering and the evening grain offering and
        the king\u2019s burnt offering and his grain offering, with the burnt offering
        of all the people of the land, and their grain offering and their drink offering.
        And throw on it all the blood of the burnt offering and all the blood of
        the sacrifice, but the bronze altar shall be for me to inquire by.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Uriah the priest did all this, as King Ahaz commanded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And King Ahaz cut off the frames of the stands and removed the basin
        from them, and he took down the sea[[COMMENT(0)]] from off the bronze oxen
        that were under it and put it on a stone pedestal. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:17 '
        content: Compare 1 Kings 7:23
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the covered way for the Sabbath that had been built inside the
        house and the outer entrance for the king he caused to go around the house
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, because of the king of Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Ahaz that he did, are they not written
        in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And Ahaz slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in
        the city of David, and Hezekiah his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hoshea Reigns in Israel'
      title: Hoshea Reigns in Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  In the twelfth year of Ahaz king of Judah, Hoshea the son of Elah
        began to reign in Samaria over Israel, and he reigned nine years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        yet not as the kings of Israel who were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Against him came up Shalmaneser king of Assyria. And Hoshea became
        his vassal and paid him tribute. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the king of Assyria found treachery in Hoshea, for he had sent
        messengers to So, king of Egypt, and offered no tribute to the king of Assyria,
        as he had done year by year. Therefore the king of Assyria shut him up and
        bound him in prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Fall of Israel'
      title: The Fall of Israel
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the king of Assyria invaded all the land and came to Samaria,
        and for three years he besieged it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Exile Because of Idolatry'
      title: Exile Because of Idolatry
      number: 6
      content: 'In the ninth year of Hoshea, the king of Assyria captured Samaria,
        and he carried the Israelites away to Assyria and placed them in Halah, and
        on the Habor, the river of Gozan, and in the cities of the Medes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And this occurred because the people of Israel had sinned against
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God, who had brought them up out of
        the land of Egypt from under the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt, and had feared
        other gods '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and walked in the customs of the nations whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        drove out before the people of Israel, and in the customs that the kings
        of Israel had practiced. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the people of Israel did secretly against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God things that were not right. They built for themselves high places
        in all their towns, from watchtower to fortified city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They set up for themselves pillars and Asherim on every high hill
        and under every green tree, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and there they made offerings on all the high places, as the nations
        did whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> carried away before them. And they
        did wicked things, provoking the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to anger, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and they served idols, of which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had
        said to them, \u201CYou shall not do this.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  warned Israel and Judah by every
        prophet and every seer, saying, \u201CTurn from your evil ways and keep my
        commandments and my statutes, in accordance with all the Law that I commanded
        your fathers, and that I sent to you by my servants the prophets.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But they would not listen, but were stubborn, as their fathers had
        been, who did not believe in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They despised his statutes and his covenant that he made with their
        fathers and the warnings that he gave them. They went after false idols and
        became false, and they followed the nations that were around them, concerning
        whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded them that they should
        not do like them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And they abandoned all the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God, and made for themselves metal images of two calves; and they made
        an Asherah and worshiped all the host of heaven and served Baal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they burned their sons and their daughters as offerings[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and used divination and omens and sold themselves to do evil in the sight
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, provoking him to anger. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:17 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was very angry with Israel
        and removed them out of his sight. None was left but the tribe of Judah only.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Judah also did not keep the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God, but walked in the customs that Israel had introduced. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rejected all the descendants
        of Israel and afflicted them and gave them into the hand of plunderers, until
        he had cast them out of his sight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  When he had torn Israel from the house of David, they made Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat king. And Jeroboam drove Israel from following the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        and made them commit great sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The people of Israel walked in all the sins that Jeroboam did. They
        did not depart from them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Assyria Resettles Samaria'
      title: Assyria Resettles Samaria
      number: 23
      content: 'until the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> removed Israel out of his sight,
        as he had spoken by all his servants the prophets. So Israel was exiled from
        their own land to Assyria until this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  And the king of Assyria brought people from Babylon, Cuthah, Avva,
        Hamath, and Sepharvaim, and placed them in the cities of Samaria instead
        of the people of Israel. And they took possession of Samaria and lived in
        its cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And at the beginning of their dwelling there, they did not fear the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent
        lions among them, which killed some of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So the king of Assyria was told, \u201CThe nations that you have
        carried away and placed in the cities of Samaria do not know the law of the
        god of the land. Therefore he has sent lions among them, and behold, they
        are killing them, because they do not know the law of the god of the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the king of Assyria commanded, \u201CSend there one of the priests
        whom you carried away from there, and let him[[COMMENT(0)]] go and dwell
        there and teach them the law of the god of the land.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '17:27 '
        content: 'Syriac, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So one of the priests whom they had carried away from Samaria came
        and lived in Bethel and taught them how they should fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'But every nation still made gods of its own and put them in the shrines
        of the high places that the Samaritans had made, every nation in the cities
        in which they lived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The men of Babylon made Succoth-benoth, the men of Cuth made Nergal,
        the men of Hamath made Ashima, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and the Avvites made Nibhaz and Tartak; and the Sepharvites burned
        their children in the fire to Adrammelech and Anammelech, the gods of Sepharvaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'They also feared the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  and appointed from
        among themselves all sorts of people as priests of the high places, who sacrificed
        for them in the shrines of the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So they feared the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> but also served their
        own gods, after the manner of the nations from among whom they had been carried
        away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'To this day they do according to the former manner. They do not fear
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and they do not follow the statutes or the
        rules or the law or the commandment that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded the children of Jacob, whom he named Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made a covenant with them and commanded
        them, \u201CYou shall not fear other gods or bow yourselves to them or serve
        them or sacrifice to them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'but you shall fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who brought you
        out of the land of Egypt with great power and with an outstretched arm. You
        shall bow yourselves to him, and to him you shall sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And the statutes and the rules and the law and the commandment that
        he wrote for you, you shall always be careful to do. You shall not fear other
        gods, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'and you shall not forget the covenant that I have made with you.
        You shall not fear other gods, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "but you shall fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, and
        he will deliver you out of the hand of all your enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'However, they would not listen, but they did according to their former
        manner.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "  So these nations feared the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and also
        served their carved images. Their children did likewise, and their children\u2019s
        children\u2014as their fathers did, so they do to this day."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Hezekiah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '    In the third year of Hoshea son of Elah, king of Israel, Hezekiah
        the son of Ahaz, king of Judah, began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Abi the daughter
        of Zechariah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he did what was right in the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        according to all that David his father had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He removed the high places and broke the pillars and cut down the
        Asherah. And he broke in pieces the bronze serpent that Moses had made, for
        until those days the people of Israel had made offerings to it (it was called
        Nehushtan).[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:4 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for both and '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He trusted in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        so that there was none like him among all the kings of Judah after him, nor
        among those who were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For he held fast to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. He did not depart
        from following him, but kept the commandments that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was with him; wherever he went
        out, he prospered. He rebelled against the king of Assyria and would not
        serve him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He struck down the Philistines as far as Gaza and its territory,
        from watchtower to fortified city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In the fourth year of King Hezekiah, which was the seventh year of
        Hoshea son of Elah, king of Israel, Shalmaneser king of Assyria came up against
        Samaria and besieged it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and at the end of three years he took it. In the sixth year of Hezekiah,
        which was the ninth year of Hoshea king of Israel, Samaria was taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The king of Assyria carried the Israelites away to Assyria and put
        them in Halah, and on the Habor, the river of Gozan, and in the cities of
        the Medes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Sennacherib Attacks Judah'
      title: Sennacherib Attacks Judah
      number: 12
      content: 'because they did not obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God but transgressed his covenant, even all that Moses the servant
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded. They neither listened nor obeyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  In the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah, Sennacherib king of Assyria
        came up against all the fortified cities of Judah and took them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Hezekiah king of Judah sent to the king of Assyria at Lachish,
        saying, \u201CI have done wrong; withdraw from me. Whatever you impose on
        me I will bear.\u201D And the king of Assyria required of Hezekiah king of
        Judah three hundred talents[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver and thirty talents of
        gold. "
      comments:
      - number: '18:14 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Hezekiah gave him all the silver that was found in the house
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and in the treasuries of the king\u2019s
        house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'At that time Hezekiah stripped the gold from the doors of the temple
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and from the doorposts that Hezekiah king
        of Judah had overlaid and gave it to the king of Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the king of Assyria sent the Tartan, the Rab-saris, and the Rabshakeh
        with a great army from Lachish to King Hezekiah at Jerusalem. And they went
        up and came to Jerusalem. When they arrived, they came and stood by the conduit
        of the upper pool, which is on the highway to the Washer\u2019s Field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And when they called for the king, there came out to them Eliakim
        the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, and Shebnah the secretary,
        and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And the Rabshakeh said to them, \u201CSay to Hezekiah, \u2018Thus
        says the great king, the king of Assyria: On what do you rest this trust
        of yours? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do you think that mere words are strategy and power for war? In whom
        do you now trust, that you have rebelled against me? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Behold, you are trusting now in Egypt, that broken reed of a staff,
        which will pierce the hand of any man who leans on it. Such is Pharaoh king
        of Egypt to all who trust in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But if you say to me, \u201CWe trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God,\u201D is it not he whose high places and altars Hezekiah has removed,
        saying to Judah and to Jerusalem, \u201CYou shall worship before this altar
        in Jerusalem\u201D? "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Come now, make a wager with my master the king of Assyria: I will
        give you two thousand horses, if you are able on your part to set riders
        on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "How then can you repulse a single captain among the least of my master\u2019s
        servants, when you trust in Egypt for chariots and for horsemen? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Moreover, is it without the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that I have
        come up against this place to destroy it? The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to me, \u201CGo up against this land and destroy it.\u201D\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, and Shebnah, and Joah, said to the
        Rabshakeh, \u201CPlease speak to your servants in Aramaic, for we understand
        it. Do not speak to us in the language of Judah within the hearing of the
        people who are on the wall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But the Rabshakeh said to them, \u201CHas my master sent me to speak
        these words to your master and to you, and not to the men sitting on the
        wall, who are doomed with you to eat their own dung and to drink their own
        urine?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then the Rabshakeh stood and called out in a loud voice in the language
        of Judah: \u201CHear the word of the great king, the king of Assyria! "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Thus says the king: \u2018Do not let Hezekiah deceive you, for he
        will not be able to deliver you out of my[[COMMENT(0)]] hand. "
      comments:
      - number: '18:29 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Do not let Hezekiah make you trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        by saying, The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will surely deliver us, and this
        city will not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Do not listen to Hezekiah, for thus says the king of Assyria: \u2018Make
        your peace with me[[COMMENT(0)]] and come out to me. Then each one of you
        will eat of his own vine, and each one of his own fig tree, and each one
        of you will drink the water of his own cistern, "
      comments:
      - number: '18:31 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "until I come and take you away to a land like your own land, a land
        of grain and wine, a land of bread and vineyards, a land of olive trees and
        honey, that you may live, and not die. And do not listen to Hezekiah when
        he misleads you by saying, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will deliver
        us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Has any of the gods of the nations ever delivered his land out of
        the hand of the king of Assyria? '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Where are the gods of Hamath and Arpad? Where are the gods of Sepharvaim,
        Hena, and Ivvah? Have they delivered Samaria out of my hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Who among all the gods of the lands have delivered their lands out
        of my hand, that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> should deliver Jerusalem
        out of my hand?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "But the people were silent and answered him not a word, for the king\u2019s
        command was, \u201CDo not answer him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, and Shebna
        the secretary, and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder, came to Hezekiah
        with their clothes torn and told him the words of the Rabshakeh.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaiah Reassures Hezekiah'
      title: Isaiah Reassures Hezekiah
      number: 1
      content: '    As soon as King Hezekiah heard it, he tore his clothes and covered
        himself with sackcloth and went into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he sent Eliakim, who was over the household, and Shebna the secretary,
        and the senior priests, covered with sackcloth, to the prophet Isaiah the
        son of Amoz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They said to him, \u201CThus says Hezekiah, This day is a day of
        distress, of rebuke, and of disgrace; children have come to the point of
        birth, and there is no strength to bring them forth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It may be that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God heard all
        the words of the Rabshakeh, whom his master the king of Assyria has sent
        to mock the living God, and will rebuke the words that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has heard; therefore lift up your prayer for the remnant that is
        left.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the servants of King Hezekiah came to Isaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Isaiah said to them, \u201CSay to your master, \u2018Thus says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Do not be afraid because of the words that you
        have heard, with which the servants of the king of Assyria have reviled me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Sennacherib Defies the '
      title: 'Sennacherib Defies the '
      number: 7
      content: "Behold, I will put a spirit in him, so that he shall hear a rumor
        and return to his own land, and I will make him fall by the sword in his
        own land.\u2019\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Rabshakeh returned, and found the king of Assyria fighting against
        Libnah, for he heard that the king had left Lachish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now the king heard concerning Tirhakah king of Cush, \u201CBehold,
        he has set out to fight against you.\u201D So he sent messengers again to
        Hezekiah, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThus shall you speak to Hezekiah king of Judah: \u2018Do not
        let your God in whom you trust deceive you by promising that Jerusalem will
        not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Behold, you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all
        lands, devoting them to destruction. And shall you be delivered? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Have the gods of the nations delivered them, the nations that my
        fathers destroyed, Gozan, Haran, Rezeph, and the people of Eden who were
        in Telassar? '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 13
      content: "Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, the king of the city
        of Sepharvaim, the king of Hena, or the king of Ivvah?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Hezekiah received the letter from the hand of the messengers and
        read it; and Hezekiah went up to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and spread it before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Hezekiah prayed before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said:
        \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, enthroned above the
        cherubim, you are the God, you alone, of all the kingdoms of the earth; you
        have made heaven and earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Incline your ear, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and hear; open your
        eyes, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and see; and hear the words of Sennacherib,
        which he has sent to mock the living God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Truly, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the kings of Assyria have laid
        waste the nations and their lands '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and have cast their gods into the fire, for they were not gods, but
        the work of men\u2019s hands, wood and stone. Therefore they were destroyed. "
      comments: []
    - name: "19: Isaiah Prophesies Sennacherib\u2019s Fall"
      title: "Isaiah Prophesies Sennacherib\u2019s Fall"
      number: 19
      content: "So now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, save us, please, from
        his hand, that all the kingdoms of the earth may know that you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        are God alone.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Isaiah the son of Amoz sent to Hezekiah, saying, \u201CThus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel: Your prayer to me
        about Sennacherib king of Assyria I have heard. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "This is the word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken
        concerning him:\u201CShe despises you, she scorns you\u2014  the virgin daughter
        of Zion;she wags her head behind you\u2014the daughter of Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CWhom have you mocked and reviled?Against whom have you raised
        your voiceand lifted your eyes to the heights?Against the Holy One of Israel!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  By your messengers you have mocked the Lord,and you have said,
        \u2018With my many chariotsI have gone up the heights of the mountains,to
        the far recesses of Lebanon;I felled its tallest cedars,its choicest cypresses;I
        entered its farthest lodging place,its most fruitful forest.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I dug wellsand drank foreign waters,and I dried up with the sole
        of my footall the streams of Egypt.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CHave you not heardthat I determined it long ago?I planned from
        days of oldwhat now I bring to pass,that you should turn fortified citiesinto
        heaps of ruins,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'while their inhabitants, shorn of strength,are dismayed and confounded,and
        have become like plants of the fieldand like tender grass,like grass on the
        housetops,blighted before it is grown.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBut I know your sitting down  and your going out and coming
        in,and your raging against me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Because you have raged against meand your complacency has come into
        my ears,I will put my hook in your noseand my bit in your mouth,and I will
        turn you back on the wayby which you came.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CAnd this shall be the sign for you: this year eat what grows
        of itself, and in the second year what springs of the same. Then in the third
        year sow and reap and plant vineyards, and eat their fruit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the surviving remnant of the house of Judah shall again take
        root downward and bear fruit upward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For out of Jerusalem shall go a remnant, and out of Mount Zion a
        band of survivors. The zeal of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will do this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning
        the king of Assyria: He shall not come into this city or shoot an arrow there,
        or come before it with a shield or cast up a siege mound against it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'By the way that he came, by the same he shall return, and he shall
        not come into this city, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "For I will defend this city to save it, for my own sake and for the
        sake of my servant David.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And that night the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> went
        out and struck down 185,000 in the camp of the Assyrians. And when people
        arose early in the morning, behold, these were all dead bodies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then Sennacherib king of Assyria departed and went home and lived
        at Nineveh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: And as he was worshiping in the house of Nisroch his god, Adrammelech
        and Sharezer, his sons, struck him down with the sword and escaped into the
        land of Ararat. And Esarhaddon his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hezekiah\u2019s Illness and Recovery"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Illness and Recovery"
      number: 1
      content: "    In those days Hezekiah became sick and was at the point of death.
        And Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz came to him and said to him, \u201CThus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018Set your house in order, for
        you shall die; you shall not recover.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Hezekiah turned his face to the wall and prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CNow, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, please remember how I have
        walked before you in faithfulness and with a whole heart, and have done what
        is good in your sight.\u201D And Hezekiah wept bitterly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And before Isaiah had gone out of the middle court, the word of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to him: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CTurn back, and say to Hezekiah the leader of my people, Thus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of David your father: I have
        heard your prayer; I have seen your tears. Behold, I will heal you. On the
        third day you shall go up to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and I will add fifteen years to your life. I will deliver you and
        this city out of the hand of the king of Assyria, and I will defend this
        city for my own sake and for my servant David\u2019s sake.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Isaiah said, \u201CBring a cake of figs. And let them take and
        lay it on the boil, that he may recover.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CWhat shall be the sign that the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will heal me, and that I shall go up to the house
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on the third day?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Isaiah said, \u201CThis shall be the sign to you from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will do the thing that he has promised:
        shall the shadow go forward ten steps, or go back ten steps?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Hezekiah answered, \u201CIt is an easy thing for the shadow to
        lengthen ten steps. Rather let the shadow go back ten steps.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Hezekiah and the Babylonian Envoys'
      title: Hezekiah and the Babylonian Envoys
      number: 11
      content: 'And Isaiah the prophet called to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and he brought the shadow back ten steps, by which it had gone down on the
        steps of Ahaz.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  At that time Merodach-baladan the son of Baladan, king of Babylon,
        sent envoys with letters and a present to Hezekiah, for he heard that Hezekiah
        had been sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Hezekiah welcomed them, and he showed them all his treasure house,
        the silver, the gold, the spices, the precious oil, his armory, all that
        was found in his storehouses. There was nothing in his house or in all his
        realm that Hezekiah did not show them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Isaiah the prophet came to King Hezekiah, and said to him, \u201CWhat
        did these men say? And from where did they come to you?\u201D And Hezekiah
        said, \u201CThey have come from a far country, from Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He said, \u201CWhat have they seen in your house?\u201D And Hezekiah
        answered, \u201CThey have seen all that is in my house; there is nothing
        in my storehouses that I did not show them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CHear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Behold, the days are coming, when all that is in your house, and
        that which your fathers have stored up till this day, shall be carried to
        Babylon. Nothing shall be left, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And some of your own sons, who will come from you, whom you will
        father, shall be taken away, and they shall be eunuchs in the palace of the
        king of Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CThe word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        that you have spoken is good.\u201D For he thought, \u201CWhy not, if there
        will be peace and security in my days?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  The rest of the deeds of Hezekiah and all his might and how he
        made the pool and the conduit and brought water into the city, are they not
        written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And Hezekiah slept with his fathers, and Manasseh his son reigned
        in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Manasseh Reigns in Judah'
      title: Manasseh Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: "    Manasseh was twelve years old when he began to reign, and he
        reigned fifty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Hephzibah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        according to the despicable practices of the nations whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        drove out before the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For he rebuilt the high places that Hezekiah his father had destroyed,
        and he erected altars for Baal and made an Asherah, as Ahab king of Israel
        had done, and worshiped all the host of heaven and served them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he built altars in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        of which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had said, \u201CIn Jerusalem will
        I put my name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he built altars for all the host of heaven in the two courts
        of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he burned his son as an offering[[COMMENT(0)]] and used fortune-telling
        and omens and dealt with mediums and with necromancers. He did much evil
        in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, provoking him to anger. '
      comments:
      - number: '21:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the carved image of Asherah that he had made he set in the house
        of which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to David and to Solomon his
        son, \u201CIn this house, and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen out of all
        the tribes of Israel, I will put my name forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And I will not cause the feet of Israel to wander anymore out of
        the land that I gave to their fathers, if only they will be careful to do
        according to all that I have commanded them, and according to all the Law
        that my servant Moses commanded them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Manasseh\u2019s Idolatry Denounced"
      title: "Manasseh\u2019s Idolatry Denounced"
      number: 9
      content: 'But they did not listen, and Manasseh led them astray to do more
        evil than the nations had done whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> destroyed
        before the people of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said by his servants the prophets, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBecause Manasseh king of Judah has committed these abominations
        and has done things more evil than all that the Amorites did, who were before
        him, and has made Judah also to sin with his idols, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel:
        Behold, I am bringing upon Jerusalem and Judah such disaster[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that the ears of everyone who hears of it will tingle. '
      comments:
      - number: '21:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I will stretch over Jerusalem the measuring line of Samaria,
        and the plumb line of the house of Ahab, and I will wipe Jerusalem as one
        wipes a dish, wiping it and turning it upside down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And I will forsake the remnant of my heritage and give them into
        the hand of their enemies, and they shall become a prey and a spoil to all
        their enemies, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "because they have done what is evil in my sight and have provoked
        me to anger, since the day their fathers came out of Egypt, even to this
        day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  Moreover, Manasseh shed very much innocent blood, till he had filled
        Jerusalem from one end to another, besides the sin that he made Judah to
        sin so that they did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh and all that he did, and the
        sin that he committed, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles
        of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Amon Reigns in Judah'
      title: Amon Reigns in Judah
      number: 18
      content: 'And Manasseh slept with his fathers and was buried in the garden
        of his house, in the garden of Uzza, and Amon his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Amon was twenty-two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        two years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Meshullemeth the daughter
        of Haruz of Jotbah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        as Manasseh his father had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He walked in all the way in which his father walked and served the
        idols that his father served and worshiped them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He abandoned the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of his fathers,
        and did not walk in the way of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the servants of Amon conspired against him and put the king to
        death in his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But the people of the land struck down all those who had conspired
        against King Amon, and the people of the land made Josiah his son king in
        his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Amon that he did, are they not written
        in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And he was buried in his tomb in the garden of Uzza, and Josiah his
        son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Josiah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Josiah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: "    Josiah was eight years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        thirty-one years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jedidah the daughter
        of Adaiah of Bozkath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Josiah Repairs the Temple'
      title: Josiah Repairs the Temple
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did what was right in the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and walked in all the way of David his father, and he did not turn aside
        to the right or to the left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In the eighteenth year of King Josiah, the king sent Shaphan the
        son of Azaliah, son of Meshullam, the secretary, to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CGo up to Hilkiah the high priest, that he may count the money
        that has been brought into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        which the keepers of the threshold have collected from the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And let it be given into the hand of the workmen who have the oversight
        of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and let them give it to
        the workmen who are at the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, repairing
        the house '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(that is, to the carpenters, and to the builders, and to the masons),
        and let them use it for buying timber and quarried stone to repair the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Hilkiah Finds the Book of the Law'
      title: Hilkiah Finds the Book of the Law
      number: 7
      content: "But no accounting shall be asked from them for the money that is
        delivered into their hand, for they deal honestly.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Hilkiah the high priest said to Shaphan the secretary, \u201CI
        have found the Book of the Law in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D
        And Hilkiah gave the book to Shaphan, and he read it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Shaphan the secretary came to the king, and reported to the king,
        \u201CYour servants have emptied out the money that was found in the house
        and have delivered it into the hand of the workmen who have the oversight
        of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Shaphan the secretary told the king, \u201CHilkiah the priest
        has given me a book.\u201D And Shaphan read it before the king.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When the king heard the words of the Book of the Law, he tore his
        clothes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the king commanded Hilkiah the priest, and Ahikam the son of
        Shaphan, and Achbor the son of Micaiah, and Shaphan the secretary, and Asaiah
        the king\u2019s servant, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CGo, inquire of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for me, and
        for the people, and for all Judah, concerning the words of this book that
        has been found. For great is the wrath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        that is kindled against us, because our fathers have not obeyed the words
        of this book, to do according to all that is written concerning us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Hilkiah the priest, and Ahikam, and Achbor, and Shaphan, and Asaiah
        went to Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of Tikvah, son
        of Harhas, keeper of the wardrobe (now she lived in Jerusalem in the Second
        Quarter), and they talked with her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And she said to them, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel: \u2018Tell the man who sent you to me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, Behold, I will bring disaster
        upon this place and upon its inhabitants, all the words of the book that
        the king of Judah has read. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Because they have forsaken me and have made offerings to other gods,
        that they might provoke me to anger with all the work of their hands, therefore
        my wrath will be kindled against this place, and it will not be quenched. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But to the king of Judah, who sent you to inquire of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        thus shall you say to him, Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the
        God of Israel: Regarding the words that you have heard, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'because your heart was penitent, and you humbled yourself before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, when you heard how I spoke against this
        place and against its inhabitants, that they should become a desolation and
        a curse, and you have torn your clothes and wept before me, I also have heard
        you, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Therefore, behold, I will gather you to your fathers, and you shall
        be gathered to your grave in peace, and your eyes shall not see all the disaster
        that I will bring upon this place.\u2019\u201D And they brought back word
        to the king."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Josiah\u2019s Reforms"
      title: "Josiah\u2019s Reforms"
      number: 1
      content: '    Then the king sent, and all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem
        were gathered to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the king went up to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and with him all the men of Judah and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem and
        the priests and the prophets, all the people, both small and great. And he
        read in their hearing all the words of the Book of the Covenant that had
        been found in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the king stood by the pillar and made a covenant before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        to walk after the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and to keep his commandments
        and his testimonies and his statutes with all his heart and all his soul,
        to perform the words of this covenant that were written in this book. And
        all the people joined in the covenant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the king commanded Hilkiah the high priest and the priests of
        the second order and the keepers of the threshold to bring out of the temple
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> all the vessels made for Baal, for Asherah,
        and for all the host of heaven. He burned them outside Jerusalem in the fields
        of the Kidron and carried their ashes to Bethel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he deposed the priests whom the kings of Judah had ordained to
        make offerings in the high places at the cities of Judah and around Jerusalem;
        those also who burned incense to Baal, to the sun and the moon and the constellations
        and all the host of the heavens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he brought out the Asherah from the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        outside Jerusalem, to the brook Kidron, and burned it at the brook Kidron
        and beat it to dust and cast the dust of it upon the graves of the common
        people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he broke down the houses of the male cult prostitutes who were
        in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, where the women wove hangings
        for the Asherah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he brought all the priests out of the cities of Judah, and defiled
        the high places where the priests had made offerings, from Geba to Beersheba.
        And he broke down the high places of the gates that were at the entrance
        of the gate of Joshua the governor of the city, which were on one\u2019s
        left at the gate of the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'However, the priests of the high places did not come up to the altar
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in Jerusalem, but they ate unleavened
        bread among their brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he defiled Topheth, which is in the Valley of the Son of Hinnom,
        that no one might burn his son or his daughter as an offering to Molech.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he removed the horses that the kings of Judah had dedicated to
        the sun, at the entrance to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        by the chamber of Nathan-melech the chamberlain, which was in the precincts.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        And he burned the chariots of the sun with fire. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:11 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the altars on the roof of the upper chamber of Ahaz, which the
        kings of Judah had made, and the altars that Manasseh had made in the two
        courts of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, he pulled down and
        broke in pieces[[COMMENT(0)]] and cast the dust of them into the brook Kidron. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:12 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the king defiled the high places that were east of Jerusalem,
        to the south of the mount of corruption, which Solomon the king of Israel
        had built for Ashtoreth the abomination of the Sidonians, and for Chemosh
        the abomination of Moab, and for Milcom the abomination of the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he broke in pieces the pillars and cut down the Asherim and filled
        their places with the bones of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Moreover, the altar at Bethel, the high place erected by Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat, who made Israel to sin, that altar with the high place
        he pulled down and burned,[[COMMENT(0)]] reducing it to dust. He also burned
        the Asherah. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:15 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And as Josiah turned, he saw the tombs there on the mount. And he
        sent and took the bones out of the tombs and burned them on the altar and
        defiled it, according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that
        the man of God proclaimed, who had predicted these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he said, \u201CWhat is that monument that I see?\u201D And the
        men of the city told him, \u201CIt is the tomb of the man of God who came
        from Judah and predicted[[COMMENT(0)]] these things that you have done against
        the altar at Bethel.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '23:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said, \u201CLet him be; let no man move his bones.\u201D So
        they let his bones alone, with the bones of the prophet who came out of Samaria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Josiah removed all the shrines also of the high places that were
        in the cities of Samaria, which kings of Israel had made, provoking the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to anger. He did to them according to all that he had done at Bethel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Josiah Restores the Passover'
      title: Josiah Restores the Passover
      number: 20
      content: 'And he sacrificed all the priests of the high places who were there,
        on the altars, and burned human bones on them. Then he returned to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the king commanded all the people, \u201CKeep the Passover to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, as it is written in this Book of
        the Covenant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For no such Passover had been kept since the days of the judges who
        judged Israel, or during all the days of the kings of Israel or of the kings
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But in the eighteenth year of King Josiah this Passover was kept
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Moreover, Josiah put away the mediums and the necromancers and the
        household gods and the idols and all the abominations that were seen in the
        land of Judah and in Jerusalem, that he might establish the words of the
        law that were written in the book that Hilkiah the priest found in the house
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Before him there was no king like him, who turned to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        with all his heart and with all his soul and with all his might, according
        to all the Law of Moses, nor did any like him arise after him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Still the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did not turn from the burning
        of his great wrath, by which his anger was kindled against Judah, because
        of all the provocations with which Manasseh had provoked him. '
      comments: []
    - name: "27: Josiah\u2019s Death in Battle"
      title: "Josiah\u2019s Death in Battle"
      number: 27
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CI will remove Judah
        also out of my sight, as I have removed Israel, and I will cast off this
        city that I have chosen, Jerusalem, and the house of which I said, My name
        shall be there.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Josiah and all that he did, are they
        not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'In his days Pharaoh Neco king of Egypt went up to the king of Assyria
        to the river Euphrates. King Josiah went to meet him, and Pharaoh Neco killed
        him at Megiddo, as soon as he saw him. '
      comments: []
    - name: "30: Jehoahaz\u2019s Reign and Captivity"
      title: "Jehoahaz\u2019s Reign and Captivity"
      number: 30
      content: "And his servants carried him dead in a chariot from Megiddo and brought
        him to Jerusalem and buried him in his own tomb. And the people of the land
        took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah, and anointed him, and made him king in his
        father\u2019s place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  Jehoahaz was twenty-three years old when he began to reign, and
        he reigned three months in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Hamutal
        the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        according to all that his fathers had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And Pharaoh Neco put him in bonds at Riblah in the land of Hamath,
        that he might not reign in Jerusalem, and laid on the land a tribute of a
        hundred talents[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver and a talent of gold. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:33 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And Pharaoh Neco made Eliakim the son of Josiah king in the place
        of Josiah his father, and changed his name to Jehoiakim. But he took Jehoahaz
        away, and he came to Egypt and died there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Jehoiakim Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jehoiakim Reigns in Judah
      number: 35
      content: 'And Jehoiakim gave the silver and the gold to Pharaoh, but he taxed
        the land to give the money according to the command of Pharaoh. He exacted
        the silver and the gold of the people of the land, from everyone according
        to his assessment, to give it to Pharaoh Neco.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "  Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and
        he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Zebidah
        the daughter of Pedaiah of Rumah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        according to all that his fathers had done.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    In his days, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up, and Jehoiakim
        became his servant for three years. Then he turned and rebelled against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent against him bands of the
        Chaldeans and bands of the Syrians and bands of the Moabites and bands of
        the Ammonites, and sent them against Judah to destroy it, according to the
        word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he spoke by his servants the
        prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Surely this came upon Judah at the command of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        to remove them out of his sight, for the sins of Manasseh, according to all
        that he had done, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and also for the innocent blood that he had shed. For he filled Jerusalem
        with innocent blood, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> would not pardon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the rest of the deeds of Jehoiakim and all that he did, are they
        not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Jehoiakim slept with his fathers, and Jehoiachin his son reigned
        in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Jehoiachin Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jehoiachin Reigns in Judah
      number: 7
      content: 'And the king of Egypt did not come again out of his land, for the
        king of Babylon had taken all that belonged to the king of Egypt from the
        Brook of Egypt to the river Euphrates.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  Jehoiachin was eighteen years old when he became king, and he reigned
        three months in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Nehushta the daughter
        of Elnathan of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Jerusalem Captured'
      title: Jerusalem Captured
      number: 9
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        according to all that his father had done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'At that time the servants of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came
        up to Jerusalem, and the city was besieged. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came to the city while his servants
        were besieging it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and Jehoiachin the king of Judah gave himself up to the king of Babylon,
        himself and his mother and his servants and his officials and his palace
        officials. The king of Babylon took him prisoner in the eighth year of his
        reign '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and carried off all the treasures of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        and the treasures of the king\u2019s house, and cut in pieces all the vessels
        of gold in the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, which Solomon king
        of Israel had made, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had foretold. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He carried away all Jerusalem and all the officials and all the mighty
        men of valor, 10,000 captives, and all the craftsmen and the smiths. None
        remained, except the poorest people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he carried away Jehoiachin to Babylon. The king\u2019s mother,
        the king\u2019s wives, his officials, and the chief men of the land he took
        into captivity from Jerusalem to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the king of Babylon brought captive to Babylon all the men of
        valor, 7,000, and the craftsmen and the metal workers, 1,000, all of them
        strong and fit for war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Zedekiah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Zedekiah Reigns in Judah
      number: 17
      content: "And the king of Babylon made Mattaniah, Jehoiachin\u2019s uncle,
        king in his place, and changed his name to Zedekiah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned
        eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Hamutal the daughter
        of Jeremiah of Libnah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        according to all that Jehoiakim had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: For because of the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> it came
        to the point in Jerusalem and Judah that he cast them out from his presence. 
        And Zedekiah rebelled against the king of Babylon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Fall and Captivity of Judah'
      title: Fall and Captivity of Judah
      number: 1
      content: '    And in the ninth year of his reign, in the tenth month, on the
        tenth day of the month, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came with all his
        army against Jerusalem and laid siege to it. And they built siegeworks all
        around it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the city was besieged till the eleventh year of King Zedekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'On the ninth day of the fourth month the famine was so severe in
        the city that there was no food for the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then a breach was made in the city, and all the men of war fled by
        night by the way of the gate between the two walls, by the king\u2019s garden,
        and the Chaldeans were around the city. And they went in the direction of
        the Arabah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the army of the Chaldeans pursued the king and overtook him in
        the plains of Jericho, and all his army was scattered from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then they captured the king and brought him up to the king of Babylon
        at Riblah, and they passed sentence on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes, and put out
        the eyes of Zedekiah and bound him in chains and took him to Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  In the fifth month, on the seventh day of the month\u2014that was
        the nineteenth year of King Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon\u2014Nebuzaradan,
        the captain of the bodyguard, a servant of the king of Babylon, came to Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he burned the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  and the
        king\u2019s house and all the houses of Jerusalem; every great house he burned
        down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And all the army of the Chaldeans, who were with the captain of the
        guard, broke down the walls around Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the rest of the people who were left in the city and the deserters
        who had deserted to the king of Babylon, together with the rest of the multitude,
        Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard carried into exile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the captain of the guard left some of the poorest of the land
        to be vinedressers and plowmen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  And the pillars of bronze that were in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and the stands and the bronze sea that were in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the Chaldeans broke in pieces and carried the bronze to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And they took away the pots and the shovels and the snuffers and
        the dishes for incense and all the vessels of bronze used in the temple service, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the fire pans also and the bowls. What was of gold the captain of
        the guard took away as gold, and what was of silver, as silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'As for the two pillars, the one sea, and the stands that Solomon
        had made for the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the bronze of
        all these vessels was beyond weight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The height of the one pillar was eighteen cubits,[[COMMENT(0)]] and
        on it was a capital of bronze. The height of the capital was three cubits.
        A latticework and pomegranates, all of bronze, were all around the capital.
        And the second pillar had the same, with the latticework.  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:17 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  And the captain of the guard took Seraiah the chief priest and
        Zephaniah the second priest and the three keepers of the threshold; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and from the city he took an officer who had been in command of the
        men of war, and five men of the king\u2019s council who were found in the
        city; and the secretary of the commander of the army, who mustered the people
        of the land; and sixty men of the people of the land, who were found in the
        city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard took them and brought them
        to the king of Babylon at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Gedaliah Made Governor of Judah'
      title: Gedaliah Made Governor of Judah
      number: 21
      content: 'And the king of Babylon struck them down and put them to death at
        Riblah in the land of Hamath. So Judah was taken into exile out of its land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And over the people who remained in the land of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon had left, he appointed Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, son of
        Shaphan, governor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now when all the captains and their men heard that the king of Babylon
        had appointed Gedaliah governor, they came with their men to Gedaliah at
        Mizpah, namely, Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, and Johanan the son of Kareah,
        and Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth the Netophathite, and Jaazaniah the son
        of the Maacathite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Gedaliah swore to them and their men, saying, \u201CDo not be
        afraid because of the Chaldean officials. Live in the land and serve the
        king of Babylon, and it shall be well with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But in the seventh month, Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, son of Elishama,
        of the royal family, came with ten men and struck down Gedaliah and put him
        to death along with the Jews and the Chaldeans who were with him at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Jehoiachin Released from Prison'
      title: Jehoiachin Released from Prison
      number: 26
      content: 'Then all the people, both small and great, and the captains of the
        forces arose and went to Egypt, for they were afraid of the Chaldeans.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  And in the thirty-seventh year of the exile of Jehoiachin king
        of Judah, in the twelfth month, on the twenty-seventh day of the month, Evil-merodach
        king of Babylon, in the year that he began to reign, graciously freed[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Jehoiachin king of Judah from prison. '
      comments:
      - number: '25:27 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he spoke kindly to him and gave him a seat above the seats of
        the kings who were with him in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So Jehoiachin put off his prison garments. And every day of his life
        he dined regularly at the king\u2019s table, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: and for his allowance, a regular allowance was given him by the king,
        according to his daily needs, as long as he lived.
      comments: []
